e1323 Investment allowance for certain investments s in the field of energy generation and distribution according to \u00a7 4a InvZulG133 - 140I Overview133 - 134II Beneficiary investments according to \u00a7 4a InvZulG135 - 1401 Beneficiary assets, expanded or newly manufactured parts and systems135 - 1372 Definition of production costs1383 \u200b\u200bRemaining and usage requirements139 - 1404 Investment allowance for investments in Berlin (West) according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG141 - 217I Overview141 - 144II Basic funding145 - 1901 Movable economic goods145 - 150a) General145b) Passenger vehicles146 - 1502 Buildings, extensions and extensions, other subsequent production work151 - 170a) Business buildings151 - 166b) Modernization measures on hotel buildings167 - 1703 Requirements for use171 - 190a) Movable economic goods171 - 185aa) General171 - 173bb) Economic goods which, by their nature, can also be used outside of a permanent establishment (excluding inland vessels) 174 - 177cc) Inland vessels178 - 185b) Immovable assets186 - 190III Special requirements for the increased investment allowance for movable assets191 - 2131"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Increased investment allowance191 - 207a) Manufacturing industry - excluding construction -191 - 201aa) Delimitation191 - 194bb) Manufacturing195 - 198cc) Data processing199 - 201b) Energy sector202 - 203c) Service industry204 - 207aa) Delimitation204bb) Data processing205cc) Distance selling206 or 4072"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Increased investment allowance208 - 2103 Conditions of stay and use211 - 213IV Special conditions for the 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Increased investment allowance for immovable assets214 - 217 Final provision - Index - The Investment Allowance Act 1986 (InvZulG 1986) in the version of the announcement of 28 January 1986 (Federal Law Gazette I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "231 - BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "56) and \u00a7 19 of the Berlin Promotion Act 1987 (BerlinFG 1987) in the version of the announcement of 10 12 1986 (Federal Law Gazette I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2415 - BStBl 1987 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "4) provide for investment grants for certain investments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The investment grants are granted from income tax or corporation tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The Investment Allowance Act and Section 19 BerlinFG are tax laws"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The terms used therein are to be interpreted in accordance with the principles governing income taxation (BFH rulings of 25 1 1985 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "309 and from 15 11 1985 - BStBl 1986 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "367)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The aforementioned laws agree in numerous individual provisions; Supreme court decisions on such individual provisions therefore apply in principle to both the Investment Allowance Act and Section 19 BerlinFG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the application of \u00a7 4b InvZulG 1982 in connection with \u00a7\u00a7 5 and 5a InvZulG 1982 in the version of the announcement of June 4, 1982 (Federal Law Gazette I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "646 - BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "562), the regulations of the BMF letter of 16 6 1982 (BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "569), dated 11 10 1982 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "775), dated 10 2 1983 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "97) and from 27 11 1986 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "547) as well as the corresponding decrees of the highest tax authorities of the states"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "When applying Sections 1 4 and 4a InvZulG 1986 in conjunction with Sections 5 5a and 8 InvZulG 1986 and Sections 19 and 20 BerlinFG 1987 in conjunction with Section 31 (19) BerlinFG 1987 apply with reference to the result of the discussions the following principles with the highest financial authorities of the federal states: Part One Common Principles A"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Substantive legal provisions I Eligible persons 1 General 1 (1) Unrestricted and limited taxpayers within the meaning of the Income Tax Act and the Corporation Tax Act as well as companies within the meaning of Section 15 (1) No. 2 EStG that make business investments in Germany are entitled to claim investment grants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the civil and economic owner of a manufactured or purchased item is not the same person, the investment allowance is to be granted to the beneficial owner (BFH judgment of 2 6 1978 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "507)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 (2) In cases of universal succession (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Inheritance, transfer of assets within the meaning of the Transformation Act), the legal successor takes the position of his legal predecessor with regard to the entitlement to claim"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if a business or partial business is transferred free of charge (Section 7 (1) EStDV) or incorporated into a corporation or partnership in accordance with Section 20 or Section 24 UmwStG; In these cases, the legal successor is entitled to the investment allowance, unless the legal predecessor has legitimately applied for it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It follows that the legal successor can claim the investment allowance even if the conditions are partly fulfilled by him and partly by his legal predecessor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 (3) The granting of the investment allowance does not depend on a specific type of profit determination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Eligible beneficiaries are therefore also eligible, whose profit is determined in accordance with Section 4 (3) EStG or average rates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Taxpayers within the meaning of the Income Tax Act and the Corporation Tax Act 4 (1) Eligibility does not require that the taxpayer is assessed with an amount or at all for income tax or corporation tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Corporations, associations of persons and estates exempt from corporation tax are entitled to claim the investment allowance, provided that they maintain an economic business and the other requirements (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "20 and 21)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "5 (2) The taxpayers within the meaning of the Corporate Income Tax Act can also include legal entities under public law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The granting of an investment allowance is only possible if they run a business of a commercial nature (Section 1 (1) No. 6 and Section 4 KStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Because of the concept of commercial operation, reference is made to Section 5 KStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "6 (3) In the case of group relationships within the meaning of Sections 14 to 19 KStG, either the controlling company or the subsidiary company is entitled to claim, depending on who fulfills the requirements for the granting of the investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 Partnerships and communities 7 (1) The eligible companies within the meaning of Section 15 (1) No. 2 EStG also include internal companies that are co-entrepreneurs, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "atypical silent societies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "8 (2) The regulation on the entitlement of companies within the meaning of Section 15 (1) No. 2 EStG applies accordingly to companies whose profits from agriculture, forestry or self-employed work are attributable to several participants (see Section 13 (5) and Section 18 (1)) 5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "9 (3) In the case of assets that belong to the special business assets of one or more shareholders, the partnership is entitled to claim"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "10 (4) General partnerships and limited partnerships that receive income from capital assets or from renting and leasing are not eligible because they have no business assets; the same applies to the investment funds of investment companies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "11 (5) Working groups, machine and laboratory groups are only to be treated as independent beneficiaries of the investment allowance if they do not fall under Section 180 (4) AO and Section 2a GewStG, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "if a separate determination of the income subject to income tax and income subject to corporation tax is to be made for them"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If an asset is acquired or manufactured by several beneficiaries for the business purposes of the co-owners without a separate determination being made, each co-owner is entitled to claim the investment allowance on a pro rata basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "II Beneficiary investments 1 General 12 (1) In the case of the individual investment grants with different requirements, 1 the acquisition and production of new, wear-and-tear movable fixed assets (\u00a7\u00a7 1 4 and 4a InvZulG, \u00a7 19 BerlinFG) are considered as beneficiary investments , 2 the production of depreciable immovable fixed assets (\u00a7\u00a7 1 4 and 4a InvZulG, \u00a7 19 BerlinFG), 3 extensions and extensions to buildings or parts of buildings belonging to the fixed assets (\u00a7\u00a7 1 4 and 4a InvZulG, \u00a7 19 BerlinFG), 4 Expansion and expansion of district heating networks as well as the acquisition and production of certain systems (Section 4a InvZulG), 5 other subsequent production work on wear-and-tear immovable fixed assets (Section 19 BerlinFG), 6 the acquisition of new, depreciable, intangible fixed assets (Section 4 InvZulG )"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "13 (2) The granting of an investment allowance is not excluded because the asset was manufactured abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Term and time of acquisition or manufacture 14 (1) Acquisition is the purchase of an asset from a third party for a fee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The transfer of an asset from current assets or from private assets to fixed assets is not a purchase (BFH judgment of 29 7 1966 - BStBl 1967 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "62)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The acquisition or manufacture of an asset can, however, be assumed if an asset that has been acquired or manufactured for the current assets is clearly before the end of the same calendar or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Financial year is transferred to fixed assets (BFH judgment of 11 12 1970 - BStBl 1971 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "198)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "15 (2) The time of purchase is the time of delivery (\u00a7 9a EStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "According to this, an asset is acquired at the point in time at which the purchaser can dispose of it economically according to the will of the contracting parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This is usually the case when ownership, risk, benefits and burdens are transferred to the purchaser (see BFH judgment of 28 4 1977 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "553)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the subject of a purchase contract for an asset is its assembly by the seller, the asset is usually only delivered once the assembly work has been completed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the assembly is carried out by the beneficiary himself or by a third party on his behalf, the time of delivery is the time at which the beneficiary has taken over the asset from the supplier"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "26 remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "16 (3) Production is the creation of a previously non-existent asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The production of an asset is completed at the time it is completed (Section 9a EStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An asset is completed as soon as it can be used for its intended purpose"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "On the question of the completion of buildings that are erected in construction phases, see the BFH judgment of 15 July 1977 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "845)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 Definition of fixed assets 17 (1) Fixed assets only include assets that are intended to serve the company on a permanent basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the intended purpose of an asset cannot be clearly determined, the accounting justifies a presumption (see Section 41c Paragraph 1 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "(2) Repair materials and spare parts are not included in fixed assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Something else only applies if it is the initial supply of spare or spare parts that were supplied or produced with the delivery or production of the asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "19 (3) Assets that are acquired or manufactured before the start of business activity belong to fixed assets from the time of acquisition or manufacture if they are intended to serve the business on a permanent basis when they are delivered or completed (see BFH rulings from 30 9 1960 - BStBl III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "489 and from 3 11 1961 - BStBl 1962 III S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "123)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This requirement can be regarded as fulfilled if the operational activity is started within one year after delivery or completion of the asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "20 (4) In the case of corporations, associations of persons and estates within the meaning of Section 1 Paragraph 1 No. 3 to 5 KStG, fixed assets can only be present if they are economically related to income within the meaning of Section 2 Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Legal persons under public law can only have fixed assets in their businesses of a commercial nature (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "21 (5) Corporations, associations of persons and estates exempt from corporation tax are only entitled to claim the investment allowance if they maintain an economic business with income within the meaning of Section 2 (1) No. 1 to 3 EStG (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for claiming the investment allowance is therefore that the fixed assets can be allocated to commercial operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if it is a purpose-built establishment within the meaning of Sections 65 to 68 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "4 Beneficiary assets a) Wearable movable assets aa) Term 22 Because of the term wearable movable assets, reference is made to Section 43 (3) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "bb) Mixing and combining of movable assets with other assets 23 (1) Assets that are built into a building belonging to the fixed assets are usually not counted as movable assets (BFH judgment of 17 5 1968 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "563)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For the acquisition or production costs of such assets, an investment allowance can therefore only be considered as part of subsidized construction costs for the building or subsidized subsequent construction costs for a building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This applies e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "for floor coverings that are fully bonded and that cannot be separated from the building without the risk of considerable damage, and for floor coverings that are loosely laid on concrete or another substrate that is usually not yet to be regarded as a finished floor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, a floor covering is laid loosely on a floor that is usually usable, it is regularly to be regarded as a movable asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "All connected floor coverings laid in a room are to be regarded as an economic asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "24 (2) Operating equipment (Section 43 Paragraph 3 EStR) and dummy components belong, contrary to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "23 are also classified as movable fixed assets if they are installed in a building belonging to the fixed assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A sham component arises when movable assets are inserted into a building for a temporary purpose through construction work (\u00a7 95 BGB)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An insertion for a temporary purpose is to be assumed if the inserted movable assets represent a considerable re-use value even after their removal and, according to the circumstances, in particular the type and purpose of the connection, it can be expected that the installed assets will be removed again later ( see BFH judgments of 24 November 1970 - BStBl 1971 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "157 and from 4 12 1970 - BStBl 1971 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "165)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Sham components are not given if the expected useful life of the installed movable assets is no longer than the period for which they are installed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Leasehold improvements or conversions can also be operating fixtures or dummy components (BMF letter of 15 1 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "66 and the corresponding decrees of the highest tax authorities of the federal states)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "25 (3) Regarding the treatment of expenses incurred by a tenant or other beneficial owner for construction work, which do not result in fictitious components or operating equipment, but which are to be treated as manufacturing costs of a wear-and-tear, immovable asset, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "33 referenced"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "26 (4) If a new movable asset is acquired or manufactured that is intended to be mixed or firmly connected with another movable asset, the acquisition or manufacture of such an asset is favored if, despite the mixing or combining, its property as retains independent movable assets as fixed assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the economic good becomes a dependent part of another movable asset by mixing or combining, then a benefit for the acquisition or production costs of the asset is only possible as part of the acquisition or production costs for the other beneficiary movable asset or as part of the subsequent production costs ( BFH rulings of 20 3 1981 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "785, dated 27 11 1981 - BStBl 1982 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "176 and from 4 12 1981 - BStBl 1984 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "630)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "cc) New assets (1) A movable asset that the claimant has produced himself is always to be regarded as \"new\" if the partial value of the used assets used in the production is 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "does not exceed the partial value of the economic good produced (BFH judgment of 4 8 1983 - BStBl 1984 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "631)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A movable economic good is always new if a new idea is realized during production and a different type of economic good is created that helps the company compete"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Then z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Construction, tool and machine shacks made from used containers new economic goods (BFH judgment of 12 6 1975 - BStBl 1976 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "96)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In contrast, an inland waterway vessel composed of the front and rear of two used ships is not a new economic asset (BFH judgment of 8 2 1980 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "341)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "28 (2) If a movable asset is acquired, it is \"new\" if it is acquired in an unused condition and the manufacturer meets the requirements that are necessary for the acceptance of a new asset in self-production (brand new)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An asset is still new if the partial value of the used assets installed in the immediate temporal and material connection with its purchase is 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "does not exceed the partial value of the uniform asset (BFH judgment of 4 12 1981 - BStBl 1984 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "630)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If a brand-new asset is initially used on a rental basis and later bought by the tenant, taking into account the rent paid, the asset is not new at the time of purchase (see BFH rulings of 24 5 1968 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "571)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Something else applies if the intention to purchase and prior testing are part of the contract and the rental period does not exceed the time appropriate for a testing (BFH judgment of 16 1 1986 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "467)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "29 (3) An asset is also not new if it was used for demonstration purposes prior to acquisition (BFH judgment of 13 3 1979 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "287)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In contrast, testing by the manufacturer to check the functionality of the asset is harmless if it does not go beyond what is necessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The condition \"new\" does not conflict with the fact that the asset is technically out of date or has been stored for a long time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "dd) Low-value and short-lived assets, depreciation allowances 30 (1) For low-value assets within the meaning of Section 6 (2) EStG, an investment allowance is not granted even if the freedom of valuation is not used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "31 (2) The granting of an investment allowance is not excluded for wear-and-tear moveable fixed assets because their useful life does not exceed 1 year (BFH judgment of 13 3 1979 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "578) or because in the year of acquisition or production due to depreciation allowances (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "according to \u00a7 4 No. 1 Inventor's Ordinance) or valued on the basis of \u00a7 6 Abs 1 No. 1 EStG with a partial value of 1 DM (BFH judgment of 28 10 1977 - BStBl 1978 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "115)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "b) Depreciable immovable assets 32 (1) Depreciable immovable assets include in particular 1 buildings, condominiums and partially owned rooms, 2 independent building parts within the meaning of Section 13b EStR, 3 outdoor facilities such as fences and ground reinforcements (e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Streets, paths, squares) and 4 specific buildings on third-party land, as well as leasehold improvements and tenant conversions (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "33), insofar as the assets referred to in numbers 2 to 4 are not operating equipment or sham components (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "33 (2) Buildings on third-party land and leasehold improvements as well as tenant conversions are a) immovable assets of the client if he is the beneficial owner of the building; this is particularly the case with tenant fixtures and fittings if the owner's claim to surrender has no economic significance (see number 6 of the BMF letter of 15 1 1976 - BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "66 and the corresponding decrees of the highest tax authorities of the federal states); b) to be treated like the builder's immovable assets if he is not the beneficial owner of the building, according to the case law of the Federal Fiscal Court (see BFH rulings of 31 10 1978 - BStBl 1979 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "399, 401 507 from 22 1 1980 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "244 and from 20 11 1980 - BStBl 1981 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "68), however, when determining the taxable profit, his expenses for the construction of the building must be treated like the production costs of a tangible asset (see BFH judgment of 10 8 1984 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "805) or the tenant fixtures or tenant conversions according to number 7 of the administrative instructions referred to under letter a are attributable to him as tangible assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "5 Beneficiaries of subsequent production work 34 (1) For the terms of the expansion and extension of buildings within the meaning of Section 1 Paragraph 3 No. 2 Section 4 Paragraph 1 and Section 4a Paragraph 1 InvZulG as well as Section 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 2 letter b double letter aa and Paragraph 2 Clause 4 No. 2 Letter a BerlinFG, the definitions in Section 17 of the Second Housing Act (Federal Law Gazette 1980 IS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "1085 - BStBl 1980 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "482) accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Extensions are accordingly to be regarded as construction measures on existing buildings through which parts of the building or rooms are redesigned with considerable construction effort so that they can be used for the intended operational purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Under expansion in this sense is the creation of operational purposes, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "by adding storeys to a building or by adding to a building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "35 (2) Because of the preferential treatment of expansions and extensions to district heating networks as well as systems for electricity or heat generation or heat recovery cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "136 to 138 36 (3) Because of the preferential treatment of subsequent manufacturing work within the meaning of Section 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 2 Letter b, double letter bb and Paragraph 2 Clause 4 No. 2 Letter b BerlinFG, see No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "152 6 Intangible assets 37 For intangible assets - with the exception of the cases of Section 4 (2) No. 3 InvZulG - an investment allowance is not granted because they belong neither to movable nor immovable assets (BFH rulings of 6 8 1964 - BStBl III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "575 and from 22 5 1979 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "634)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the concept of an intangible asset, please refer to Section 31a EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "7 Movable assets that are used exclusively or almost exclusively for operational purposes 38 (1) An investment allowance can in principle also be granted if the external use of up to 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of the total use (BFH judgments of 4 11 1977 - BStBl 1978 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "353, from 7 3 1980 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "412 and BStBl 1981 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "43 as well as from 31 7 1981 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "772)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply if exclusive use for specific operational purposes is required by law (cf. \u00a7 4 Paragraph 2 No. 1 and \u00a7 4a Paragraph 3 InvZulG as well as \u00a7 19 Paragraph 1 No. 1 Letter b BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "39 (2) If an employer gives his employee a motor vehicle for use within the framework of the employment relationship, it will be used in the employer's business to that extent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant how long the employee is left with the vehicle and to what extent he uses it privately (BFH judgment of 23 May 1986 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "919)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "8 Three-year period 40 (1) The purchased or manufactured assets or parts of assets are only beneficiary if they are at least three years after their acquisition or manufacture in the business premises of the beneficiary (\u00a7 1 Paragraph 3 No. 1 InvZulG, in the business of the beneficiary (\u00a7 4 Paragraph 2 No. 1 and 3 \u00a7 4a Paragraph 2 InvZulG) or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "remain in a permanent establishment in Berlin (West) (Section 19 BerlinFG); insofar as a certain operational use is required by law, this must also be given"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The stated conditions of residence and use must exist without interruption"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "41 (2) \"Remaining\" means a permanent spatial relationship between the asset and the establishment (permanent establishment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, this does not always require that the economic asset must remain in the spatially delimited area of \u200b\u200bthe establishment (the establishment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "According to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "113 and 174 to 185, an investment allowance can therefore also be considered for economic goods which, by their nature, are not intended to be used in the company (in the permanent establishment) of the beneficiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the BFH decisions of May 23, 1986 on Section 4b InvZulG 1982 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "916 and 918) go beyond these exceptions, they cannot be transferred to the cases of \u00a7\u00a7 1 4 and 4a InvZulG and \u00a7 19 BerlinFG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "42 (3) The requirement to remain and use is fundamentally not fulfilled if assets are removed from the company or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "to leave the business premises of the beneficiary through the following processes: 1 sale a) by way of individual sale, b) as part of the transfer of the business (business premises) against payment, 2 leasing or leasing a) by way of individual letting or single leasing, b) within the framework the leasing and leasing of the business (the permanent establishment), 3 transfer a) to another business (another permanent establishment, b) to the current assets or c) to the private assets of the beneficiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "43 (4) Because of the special features of the individual investment grants, reference is made to Section 1 InvZulG in relation to Section 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "111 to 114 with regard to \u00a7 4 InvZulG on no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "115 to 116 with regard to \u00a7 4a InvZulG on no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "139 and with regard to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "171 to 190 and No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "211 to 213"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "44 (5) In cases of universal succession (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Inheritance, transfer of assets within the meaning of the Transformation Act), the free transfer of a business or part of a business (\u00a7 7 Paragraph 1 EStDV) and the contribution according to \u00a7 20 or \u00a7 24 UmwStG are the periods in which an asset belongs to the business premises of the legal predecessor when determining the three-year period and to be added to the permanent establishment of the legal successor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "45 (6) In the event of a business split (see BMF letter of 10 12 1985 - BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "683 as well as the corresponding decrees of the highest tax authorities of the federal states), it is harmless if favored assets of the holding company are used within the three-year period in a permanent establishment of the operating company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, the holding company is entitled to claim the investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the business split already exists or is being newly established"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to the transfer of assets between the owner and operating company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "46 (7) A harmful transfer of the business (the permanent establishment) within the meaning of no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "42 No. 1 letter b is equivalent to a 100% change of shareholders in a partnership if it takes place in a uniform economic process (see BFH judgment of 25 7 1968 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "759, 760)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A harmful rental within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "42 No. 2 letter a also applies to leasing cases, unless the leased item is attributable to the lessee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "47 (8) A detrimental interruption of the three-year period occurs in any case when the company (permanent establishment) ceases its advertising activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Only the opening of bankruptcy or the decision to liquidate without cessation of the advertising activity is harmless"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "48 (9) A harmful interruption of the three-year period is also to be assumed if assets leave the permanent establishment prematurely for reasons that are only in the permanent establishment (see BFH judgment of 14 10 1977 - Federal Tax Gazette 1978 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "204)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This is e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the case if assets are sold before the end of the relevant three-year period due to a business changeover, even if the business changeover is due to a fire in the premises (BFH judgment of 2 5 1980 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "758)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "49 (10) A premature withdrawal of assets is to be regarded as harmless as an exception if the useful life of the asset has expired (cf. BFH judgment of 9 3 1967 - BStBl III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "238), due to force majeure (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "by fire, theft, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": ") or through economic consumption or a total loss (BFH judgments of 15 10 1976 - BStBl 1977 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "59 and from 1 7 1977 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "793) is initiated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to a movable asset that is exchanged for another of the same or better quality because it is defective and therefore cannot be used in the company (BFH judgment of 8 3 1968 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "430)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "9 Obligation to record 50 (1) The granting of an investment allowance in accordance with the Investment Allowance Act presupposes that the beneficiary investments have been recorded in a special register, stating the date of delivery or completion and the acquisition, production or subsequent production costs, unless this information is provided are evident from the bookkeeping or from the application for investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "51 (2) If the investment allowance is already used for down payments or partial production costs, paragraph 1 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "III Calculation of the investment allowance 1 Assessment base a) General 52 (1) The investment allowance is granted for the investments that are benefited from a financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It must be measured separately for each type of investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The assessment basis is the sum of the acquisition or production costs for eligible movable assets that were delivered or completed in the financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Production costs for subsidized immovable assets that were completed in the financial year, production costs for subsidized subsequent production work that was completed in the financial year, and acquisition costs for subsidized intangible assets that were delivered in the financial year (\u00a7 4 InvZulG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The assessment basis can also include the advance payments made in the financial year for acquisition costs for preferential movable assets and the partial production costs incurred in the financial year for eligible movable and immovable assets and for favorable subsequent production work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, in the financial year of delivery or completion of the assets or the termination of subsequent production work, only the acquisition or production costs less the down payments or partial production costs are part of the assessment basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "53 (2) If assets are admissibly valued at a fixed value, the acquisition or production costs of these assets and not the fixed value must be taken into account when determining the assessment basis (see BFH judgment of 29 7 1966 - BStBl 1967 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "151)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "54 (3) The provision of Section 4 (5) No. 7 EStG must be taken into account when determining the assessment basis (BFH judgment of 19 6 1975 - BStBl 1976 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "97)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This means that, in the case of the investment allowance, that part of the acquisition or production costs of an economic good affecting the way of life may not be included in the assessment basis which, according to the general public opinion, is to be regarded as inappropriate and is therefore not deductible business expenses according to Section 4 (5) No. 7 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Section 20 (22) sentence 2 EStR and the BFH rulings of 2 2 1979 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "387) and from 2 2 1980 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "340) is pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "55 (4) The acquisition or production costs as well as the down payments on the acquisition costs, the partial production costs and the subsequent production costs are paid for by subsidies from public or private funds (see Section 34 of the Income Tax Regulation) and by the transfer of hidden reserves (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "due to \u00a7 6b EStG or section 35 EStR) not reduced"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "56 (5) For the question of whether sales tax is part of the acquisition or production costs, Section 9b EStG must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "b) Acquisition costs 57 (1) Acquisition costs are all expenses that are incurred in order to acquire an asset and to get it ready for operation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the purchase price, minus the purchase price reductions, this includes all expenses in connection with the acquisition and relocation of the asset to an operational state, provided that they can be individually assigned to the asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The acquisition costs do not include the financing (fundraising) costs, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Loan costs, partial payment surcharges (see BFH judgment of 24 5 1968 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "574)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "58 (2) Acquisition costs for an asset that arise after the end of the financial year in which it is delivered must be taken into account when calculating the investment allowance for the financial year in which it was delivered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, it is not objectionable if such acquisition costs are only claimed for the financial year in which they arise"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "59 (3) The acquisition costs are reduced through price reductions (discounts, rebates or similar) (BFH judgment of 13 August 1957 - BStBl III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "349)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Voluntarily returned price reductions do not increase the acquisition costs (BFH judgment of 12 3 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "527)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "60 (4) In the case of purchase transactions in a foreign currency, the assessment basis for the investment allowance is the purchase price converted into German marks at the rate at the time of purchase (BFH judgment of 16 12 1977 - BStBl 1978 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "233)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "c) Production costs 61 (1) Because of the concept of production costs, reference is made to Sections 33, 33a and 58 of the Income Tax Regulation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "According to this, production costs are all expenses that arise from the consumption of goods and the use of services for the production of an asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The production costs of an asset therefore also include the acquisition costs of movable assets, insofar as they are purchased as intended for the production of an asset (BFH judgment of 20 3 1981 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "785)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For production costs that are incurred in the economic context of the production, but after the completion of an asset, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Expenses for the external plastering of a building, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "58 accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "62 (2) Expenses that can, but do not have to be included in the production costs according to Section 33 EStR, are included in the production costs for the assessment of the investment allowance if they have been treated as part of the production costs by the beneficiary for income taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The right to choose whether expenses should or should not be included in the production costs of an asset can therefore only be exercised uniformly for the investment allowance and for income taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "63 (3) Immovable fixed assets are only favored if the beneficiary has incurred manufacturing costs for them"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Therefore only the production and not the acquisition of immovable assets is favored"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Manufacturing costs are also involved in the construction of prefabricated houses and other prefabricated buildings"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If immovable fixed assets have been acquired in an unfinished state, only the expenses of the purchaser for completion are included in the production costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "As far as the BFH judgment of 19 7 1979 (BStBl 1980 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3) if something else results, this judgment does not apply beyond the decided case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "d) Advance payments 64 Because of the concept of advance payments on acquisition costs and because of the point in time at which an advance payment was made, reference is made to Section 45 (4) EStR and Section 7a (2) sentences 3 to 5 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "e) Partial production costs 65 (1) Partial production costs are the expenses incurred up to the end of the financial year through the consumption of goods and the use of services for the production of an asset (BFH judgment of 15 November 1985 - BStBl 1986 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "367)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether or not corresponding payments have already been made in the financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The partial production costs of a building also include the expenses for the construction material delivered to the construction site by the end of the financial year but not yet installed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "66 (2) Advance payments on partial production costs are not favored (BFH judgment of 10 3 1982 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "426)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Even in the case of partial payments by a claimant to an entrepreneur whom he has commissioned to produce a building object as a general contractor at a fixed price, only the partial production costs actually incurred are therefore included in the assessment basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "As far as the partial payments are based on the construction progress, they can serve as a guide for the amount of the partial production costs incurred for reasons of simplification"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "f) Production costs for subsequent production work 67 To the extent that subsequent production work is favored (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "34 136 to 138 and 152), the production costs for the subsequent production work are also part of the assessment basis for the investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Because of the concept of production costs, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "61 to 63 pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Production costs for subsequent production work are also acquisition-related expenses, which are to be treated as production costs in accordance with Section 157 (5) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "1 Amount of the investment allowance 68 The investment allowance is calculated separately for each financial year and for each type of investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The following overview shows the amount of the individual investment allowances, based on the assessment base or the relevant part of the assessment base: a) Investment allowance according to \u00a7 1 InvZulG aa) for investments in the border area 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "bb) for investments in the other areas in need of support 875 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "b) Investment allowance according to \u00a7 4 InvZulG, aa) as far as the acquisition or production costs do not exceed 500,000 DM, 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "bb) as far as the acquisition or production costs exceed DM 500,000, 75 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "c) Investment allowance according to \u00a7 4a InvZulG 75 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "b) Investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG aa) for that part of the assessment base that is attributable to movable assets within the meaning of \u00a7 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 1 Letter b BerlinFG, provided the acquisition or production costs do not exceed 500,000 DM, 40%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "if the acquisition or production costs exceed DM 500,000, 30 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "in the sense of \u00a7 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 1 Letter a BerlinFG is not applicable, 25 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "bb) for the part of the assessment base that is attributable to movable assets within the meaning of Section 19 Paragraph 1 Sentence 3 No. 1 BerlinFG, unless a higher preferential treatment is permitted, 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "cc) for the part of the assessment base that is attributable to immovable assets, extensions and extensions as well as subsequent production work on immovable assets within the meaning of \u00a7 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 2 BerlinFG, 25 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "in the sense of \u00a7 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 3 No. 2 BerlinFG is not applicable, 20 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Due to special features of the individual investment grants, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "127 to 132 as well as paragraphs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "187 190 209 and 215 to 217 pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 Cumulation of investment grants 69 The investment grants according to \u00a7\u00a7 1 4 and 4a InvZulG can be granted for an asset, an expansion or an extension side by side"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG can be granted in addition to an investment allowance according to \u00a7 4a InvZulG, but not in addition to an investment allowance according to \u00a7 1 or \u00a7 4 InvZulG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Procedural regulations I Application 1 Application deadline 70 The application for investment allowance can only be submitted up to 9 months after the end of the calendar year in which the financial year of the acquisition or manufacture of beneficial assets, the termination of beneficial subsequent manufacturing work or the preferential advance payments on acquisition costs or the favored partial production costs ends (Section 5 (3) sentence 3 InvZulG, Section 19 (5) sentence 3 BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to preferential investments that have already been made before the opening of operations (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Failure to meet the statutory application deadline leads to the loss of the right to apply, unless reinstatement in the previous status is to be granted in accordance with Section 110 AO (see BFH judgment of 7 11 1975 - BStBl 1976 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "225)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The application can be made legally effective even before the end of the relevant calendar year (BFH judgment of 23 7 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "759)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Responsible tax office 71 The application for investment allowance must be submitted to the tax office responsible for granting the investment allowance (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "82 and 83) (BFH judgment of 10 6 1975 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "762)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If, for reasons of simplification, the granting of the investment allowance is different from the one in no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "82 designated tax office responsible (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "83 sentence 1), the application can also be submitted to the person listed in para"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "82 designated tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 Form and content of the application 72 (1) The application for an investment allowance must be submitted using the officially prescribed form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In the application, the assets and subsequent production work for which an investment allowance is claimed must be specified in sufficient detail within the application period so that they can be determined during a follow-up examination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This also applies in the event that an investment allowance is requested for down payments on acquisition costs or for partial production costs (BFH judgment of 30 3 1979 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "450)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The application is only effective if it has been signed by the claimant or his representative within the application period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An application signed by the representative of the beneficiary within the application period must be supplemented by the personal signature of the beneficiary before the investment allowance notice is issued"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This handwritten signature cannot be dispensed with, as the declarations of intent required in the application form (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "with regard to the further temporal commitment of assets to a permanent establishment or to a company) and the declarations with criminal relevance for the claimant can only be made by himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "73 (1) If a certificate from the Federal Minister for Economic Affairs or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of the Federal Office of Economics (\u00a7\u00a7 1 and 4a InvZulG) or another authority (\u00a7 4 InvZulG), the application must be accompanied by the original certificate from the competent authority with a copy of the application for issuance of this certificate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the certificate is not yet available at the time the application is submitted, it must be submitted later"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "74 (3) If the application for investment allowance does not list economic goods or subsequent production work during the financial year, their designation can be made up within the application period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, this only applies as long as a decision on the investment subsidy has not yet been issued for the financial year or can still be changed according to the procedural regulations (see BFH judgment of 19 10 1984 - BStBl 1985 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "63)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "75 (4) The application must also state all further eligibility requirements, in particular the acquisition costs, production costs, down payments on acquisition costs and partial production costs of the beneficiary investments for which the investment allowance is requested"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This information can also be retrieved, supplemented or corrected after the application period has expired, as long as an investment allowance notice has not yet been issued for the financial year or can still be changed according to the procedural regulations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "II Granting of the investment allowance 1 certification procedure (\u00a7\u00a7 2 4 and 4a InvZulG) 76 (1) In the cases of \u00a7 1 in conjunction with \u00a7 2 InvZulG, \u00a7 4 Paragraph 2 No. 3 InvZulG and \u00a7 4a InvZulG, an investment allowance is granted Not only dependent on tax law, but also on business law requirements (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "100 122 and 133)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The decision that the commercial law requirements are met is made by issuing a certificate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This certificate is a substantive prerequisite for the granting of the investment allowance (see BFH decision of 25 5 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "564)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "77 (2) The economic authorities are solely responsible for deciding on the economic law requirements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The certificate is therefore not subject to review by the tax authorities and tax courts, neither in fact nor in legal terms (BFH judgment of August 29, 1986 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "920)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In the event of disputes in the certification procedure, the administrative legal process is available"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "78 (3) The certificate is a basic decision within the meaning of Section 171 (10) AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It is binding for the tax authorities and tax courts insofar as it contains value judgments outside of tax law, but not insofar as it specifically assesses tax law issues or a certain assessment of such issues is required (see BFH judgment of 19 3 1981 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "538)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Since the certificate is a non-tax administrative act, the tax statute of limitations does not apply to it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The certificate can therefore still be issued or withdrawn after the deadlines set for basic tax assessments have expired"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The certificate is binding as long as it is not withdrawn in whole or in part by the responsible economic authorities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "79 (4) If the tax office determines that the commercial law requirements specified in the certificate are obviously not present or that a condition subsequent in the certificate has occurred or a condition has not been met, it must cause the issuing authority to review the certificate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "80 (5) If the tax office determines that the investment project certified in accordance with \u00a7 2 InvZulG and the investment project carried out are not identical in terms of location, type and scope, or if there is any doubt as to their identity, the certification authority shall have the authority to review the certificate issued request (see Section 2 Paragraph 6 InvZulG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Doubts can arise in particular if there are significant deviations from the investments specified in the application for the issuance of the certificate with regard to the type of investments carried out or if the investment amount specified in the certificate is significantly higher or lower than the sum that is decisive for the assessment of the investment allowance Acquisition or manufacturing costs of the beneficiary investments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Item 105 remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "81 (6) If the tax office determines that the assets designated in the certificate according to \u00a7 4 or \u00a7 4a InvZulG and the assets actually purchased or manufactured as well as expanded or newly manufactured parts of assets are not identical, it does not have to grant an investment allowance or to reclaim and to inform the certifying authority"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the tax office has doubts about the identity, it must ask the certification authority to review the certificate issued"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Determination procedure a) Responsible tax office 82 (1) The tax office responsible for granting the investment subsidy is of \u00a7 15 Paragraph 1 No. 2 EStG and in the case of companies whose profits from agriculture and forestry or self-employed work are attributable to several participants, the tax office responsible for the separate determination of the income (\u00a7 18 Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 3 in conjunction with \u00a7 180 Paragraph 1 No. 2 Letter a AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Sentence 1 no.2 also applies if the investment allowance is applied for for assets that are special business assets (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "83 (2) For the sake of simplicity, the investment allowance is granted by the tax office responsible for the separate determination to those entitled to claim whose income from agriculture and forestry, commercial operations or self-employed work is to be determined separately in accordance with Section 180 (1) No. 2 (b) AO (\u00a7 18 Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 3 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply if a) separate determinations are to be carried out for the beneficiary by several tax offices in accordance with Section 180 Paragraph 1 No. 2 Letter b AO or b) the object of the commercial operation is the rental of holiday apartments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Working groups, machine groups, laboratory groups and similar communities for which no separate determinations need to be made (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "11), the investment allowance is granted by the tax office responsible for sales taxation of the community (\u00a7 21 AO) for reasons of simplicity, provided that the community has carried out favorable investments in the name and for the account of all parties involved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In the cases of sentences 1 and 3, the tax office responsible for the beneficiary under paragraph 1 must be notified of the granting of the investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "b) Investment allowance notice 84 (1) The provisions of the tax code applicable to tax assessment are to be applied accordingly (Section 5 (5) InvZulG and Section 19 (7) BerlinFG in conjunction with Section 155 (6) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "85 (2) Each investment allowance is to be set separately from the other investment allowances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The setting of an investment allowance is therefore not precluded by the fact that a decision on another investment allowance is already final"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "When determining the investment allowance, all investments benefiting from a financial year for which a legally valid application has been submitted at the time of the determination must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "86 (3) An investment allowance may not be set before the end of the relevant calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Economic goods and subsequent production work that the beneficiary has not specified in detail or for which the beneficiary does not provide evidence or credible evidence that the other requirements necessary for the beneficiary are met are not to be taken into account when calculating the investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "87 (4) If down payments for acquisition costs or partial production costs have been taken into account when determining the assessment basis, the investment allowance is to be set provisionally in accordance with Section 165 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In these cases it must be monitored whether the economic goods and subsequent production work are also being delivered or completed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If it is found that down payments for acquisition costs or partial production costs have been taken into account in whole or in part, for example,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "because the corresponding economic goods have not been delivered or completed or other requirements have not been met (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "128 and 132), the investment allowance notice is to be changed or canceled (Section 165 (2) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "88 (5) In cases in which the existence of the prerequisites for the granting of the investment allowance cannot be conclusively checked, the investment allowance according to \u00a7 164 AO is to be set subject to the review"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "89 (6) In the case of communities for which no separate determinations are made, a uniform notification can be issued in which the names of the participants and the shares of the investment allowance allocated to them must be included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The investment allowance notice must be made known to everyone involved, unless an authorized recipient is named"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The investment grant must be paid out proportionally to each participant, unless the participants have named a joint beneficiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "c) Repeal and amendment of the investment allowance notice 90 (1) The reclaim of investment allowance requires the repeal or a change of the investment allowance notice, which leads to a reduction of the fixed investment allowance (BFH judgment of 16 1 1986 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "467)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The provisions of Sections 129 and 172 to 177 AO applicable to the correction, cancellation and amendment of tax assessments are to be applied accordingly (Section 5 (5) InvZulG and Section 19 (7) BerlinFG in conjunction with Section 155 (6) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An investment allowance notice, even if it is final, must always be revoked or changed if assets have left the business of the beneficiary within the three-year period specified in Sections 1 4 and 4a InvZulG (permanent establishment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "have not been used to the required extent for beneficial purposes (Section 5 (6) InvZulG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to an investment allowance notice according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG if the conditions of residence and use specified in this provision are not met (\u00a7 19 (8) BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "91 (2) An investment allowance notice that has been issued subject to review can be revoked or changed without restriction, as long as the reservation is effective (Section 164 AO) and provided Section 176 AO does not prevent the cancellation or amendment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The same applies if an investment allowance notice has been issued as a provisional notice, as far as and as long as the provisional nature lasts (\u00a7 165 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "92 (3) The deadline for setting the investment allowance begins at the end of the calendar year in which the application is submitted (Section 170 (3) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It is four years (Section 169 (2) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The fixing period does not expire before the final decision on the application has been made (Section 171 (3) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If a certificate is a prerequisite for setting an investment allowance and if this certificate is withdrawn, the period for setting the investment allowance notice does not end before one year after the decision on the withdrawal of the certificate has been announced (Section 171 (10) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "93 (4) The conclusions from the withdrawal of the certificate are to be drawn regardless of whether the withdrawal is final"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "After contesting the withdrawal of the certificate, the execution of the notice of cancellation or amendment of the investment allowance is to be suspended (see Section 361 (3) AO), unless the immediate execution of the withdrawing administrative act has been ordered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "III Further procedural provisions 1 Admissibility of equity measures 94 According to Section 5 (5) sentence 2 InvZulG and Section 19 (7) BerlinFG, a corresponding application of Section 163 AO to the investment subsidy is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This means that an investment allowance may not be granted for reasons of equity and may not be set higher than is possible for legal reasons (BFH judgment of December 2, 1977 - BStBl 1978 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "272)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, the provisions on deferral and remission (\u00a7\u00a7 222 227 AO) apply accordingly to the investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "From this it follows that in individual cases, for reasons of equity, deferral of claims for repayment of an investment allowance can be granted or repayment can be waived in whole or in part"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, the repayment can also be waived in such a way that an amendment to an investment allowance notice for the purpose of reducing the investment allowance is dispensed with (see BFH judgment of 10 6 1975 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "789)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Deferment of due taxes with regard to investment allowance claims that become due later 95 Offsetting by the taxpayer with investment allowance that has not yet been set against due taxes is not possible (Section 226 (3) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, with regard to an expected investment allowance, taxes due can be deferred upon application in accordance with \u00a7 222 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for this is that a timely application for an investment allowance and all information and documents required to determine the investment allowance (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "72 to 75) are available"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, in accordance with Section 234 (2) AO, deferral interest is not set"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Before the expiry of the"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "70 of the relevant calendar year, deferral is not possible, even if the investment allowance application has already been submitted before the end of this calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 Assignment, attachment and pledging of claims to investment allowance 96 A claim to investment allowance can be assigned, pledged and attached as soon as it has arisen in accordance with Section 46 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The entitlement arises at the end of the calendar year in which the financial year of the beneficiary investments ends, but in the cases of \u00a7\u00a7 1 4 or 4a InvZulG at the earliest as soon as the certificate required by these provisions is available"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "4 Interest and late payment surcharges 97 (1) As a rule, a period of one month after notification of the notice of cancellation or amendment is to be set for the repayment of an investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Interest is charged on the claim for repayment (Section 5 (7) InvZulG, Section 19 (9) BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The interest run begins on the day the investment subsidy is paid out, in the cases of Section 5 (6) InvZulG and Section 19 (8) BerlinFG on the day on which the conditions for the repeal or amendment of the investment subsidy notice are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The interest run ends when the due date expires"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If payment is made before the due date, the interest run ends on the day of payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The interest for each full month is 05 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the repayment amount rounded down to a full hundred German marks (Section 238 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "They must be rounded down to full DM amounts (Section 8 (1) sentence 1 KBV); Amounts below DM 20 are not determined (Section 239 (2) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "98 (2) If the investment allowance is not paid back by the due date, late payment surcharges are forfeited (Section 240 AO in conjunction with Section 5 Paragraph 5 InvZulG and Section 19 Paragraph 9 BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the repayment claim is deferred, deferred interest will be charged according to \u00a7 234 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In the case of suspension of execution, the interest obligation is based on \u00a7 237 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If an investment allowance is granted by a legally binding court decision or a notice of annulment or amendment is revoked or changed in favor of the beneficiary, the investment allowance to be granted or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "interest on the amount to be paid back according to \u00a7 236 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "5 Prosecution of criminal offenses 99 Incorrect or incomplete information with regard to the granting of an investment allowance can be considered subsidy fraud under Section 264 of the Criminal Code in the version of the First Act to Combat Economic Crimes of 29 July 1976 (Federal Law Gazette I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2034, BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "433) be punishable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, the tax office is the prosecution authority (\u00a7 5a InvZulG, \u00a7 20 BerlinFG); it determines the facts of the matter and carries out the preliminary investigation independently within the limits of \u00a7 399 Paragraph 1 AO and \u00a7\u00a7 400 401 AO, if the act does not also violate other criminal laws"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Second part The individual investment grants A"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Investment allowance for investments in the border area and in other areas in need of support according to \u00a7 1 InvZulG I Overview 100 (1) The economic law requirement for the granting of an investment allowance is that an investment project is carried out which 1 is conceptually an establishment, an extension, a conversion or a fundamental one Rationalization of a permanent establishment (subsidized investment project) is to be considered, 2 is located in an area in need of support, 3 is economically particularly worthy of support and corresponds to the goals and principles of spatial planning and regional planning"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Evidence of these requirements must be provided by means of a certificate (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "76 to 81)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "101 (2) In addition to the certificate, one of the tax law requirements is that 1 favorable investments are made in the fixed assets of a commercial establishment as part of the investment project (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "102), 2 the permanent establishment is attributable to the beneficiary (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "103), 3 it concerns investments that are related to the certified investment project (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "104 to 108) and have not been concluded before applying for the certificate according to \u00a7 2 InvZulG (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "109), 4 in the case of the conversion or fundamental rationalization of a permanent establishment in the border area, the investments do not serve to procure replacements (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "110) and 5 the remaining and usage requirements within the meaning of Section 1 (3) InvZulG are met (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "111 to 114)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "II Favorable investments according to \u00a7 1 InvZulG 1 Definition of commercial permanent establishment 102 The definition of permanent establishment in \u00a7 12 AO is decisive for the term permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, several permanent establishments of a business of the taxpayer in the same municipality are considered to be a single permanent establishment (Section 1 Paragraph 1 Sentence 2 InvZulG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For the term commercial enterprise see \u00a7 2 Abs 2 and 3 GewStG as well as Sections 18 to 20 GewStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A multi-municipality permanent establishment (see Section 30 GewStG) is a uniform permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It should be noted, however, that only investment projects carried out in commercial premises are eligible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Regarding the concept of a commercial establishment when renting out tourism facilities, see Section 137 (3) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Allocation to an own permanent establishment 103 The specific tax law questions also include whether the investment project named in the certificate was carried out in the applicant's own permanent establishment (see BFH judgment of 19 3 1981 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "538)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The review of this requirement is particularly necessary in the case of a tax group"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 Affiliation of investments with the beneficiary investment project 104 (1) An investment allowance is only eligible for beneficiary investments that are related to a beneficiary investment project in a material and temporal context"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "105 (2) There is only a factual connection to the extent that assets are acquired or manufactured for the investment project specified in the certificate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, the factual context is missing if, on the occasion of a relocation or expansion of the permanent establishment, a departing asset is replaced by another of the same type, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the sold by the replacement car purchased"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "106 (3) If an area has been newly included in the group of areas in need of support, tourist areas or priority locations from a certain point in time, assets, extensions and expansions that were acquired or produced before this point in time are not related to the certified investment projects"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "107 (4) If the membership of an area to the areas requiring assistance or to the tourist areas is limited or if an area is excluded from the group of areas requiring assistance or the tourist areas, the beneficiary investment project shall only include economic assets, developments and extensions that are up to Can be purchased or manufactured within the deadline specified in the certificate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "108 (5) For assets, extensions and expansions, which according to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "104 to 107 do not belong to the certified investment project, the investment allowance is not to be granted or reclaimed due to the lack of connection with the investment project"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "109 (6) If the application for the issuance of a certificate according to \u00a7 2 InvZulG was made after June 30, 1986, an investment allowance may not be granted if investments were completed before the application was submitted (\u00a7 1 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 \u00a7 8 (2) sentence 2 InvZulG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Movable and immovable assets that were completed before the application date, movable assets that were delivered before this point in time, and extensions and extensions that were completed before this point in time are excluded from the granting of the investment allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "4 Replacement procurement in the event of conversion and fundamental rationalization 110 The investment allowance may not be granted in the event of conversion or fundamental rationalization of a commercial establishment located on the edge of the zone (Section 1 (2) InvZulG) if the investments serve to procure replacement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A replacement procurement does not exist if the purchased or manufactured asset has a different meaning for the company than the asset that has been disposed of because of its technical superiority or more efficient way of working"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A passenger car that is purchased as a replacement for a retired or retired passenger car is, however, also to be regarded as a replacement if it has a higher performance than the retired passenger car"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "5 Prerequisites for Remaining and Use 111 (1) For the granting of the investment allowance according to Section 1 InvZulG, only 1 movable assets that remain as fixed assets in the business premises of the beneficiary for at least three years after their acquisition or manufacture (Section 1 Paragraph 3 No. 1 InvZulG), and 2 immovable assets as well as extensions and extensions to buildings or parts of buildings belonging to the fixed assets, which are used by the beneficiary exclusively for internal purposes at least three years after their construction (Section 1 (3) No. 2 InvZulG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "112 (2) Regarding the remaining and usage requirements, cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "40 to 49 113 (3) In the case of means of transport, in particular motor vehicles and motor vehicle trailers, the requirement of three years' stay in the business premises is also fulfilled if they are predominantly and regularly in each year of the three-year period, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "be used without major interruptions, in traffic within the areas in need of support or to and from these areas (see BFH judgments of 17 5 1968 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "570 and from 11 6 1969 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "516)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If, in the case of motor vehicles, the period between leaving the areas requiring assistance and re-entering these areas is not more than 14 days, it can always be assumed that there is no major interruption"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to containers and swap bodies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "114 (4) If the use of a building changes during the relevant three-year period in such a way that it is partially no longer used for internal purposes, the requirements for the investment allowance do not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The part used unchanged for internal purposes (cf. Section 13b Paragraph 2 EStR) continues to benefit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Investment allowance for research and development investments according to \u00a7 4 InvZulG I Favored investments according to \u00a7 4 InvZulG 1 Group of beneficiary assets 115 (1) In addition to movable and immovable assets as well as expanded and expanded parts of buildings, immaterial assets are also benefited"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The assets and the removed or newly manufactured parts must be used for research or development to a certain extent at least 3 years after their acquisition or manufacture in the company of the beneficiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Due to the different scope of the usage requirements, cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 116 (2) Regarding the remaining and usage requirements, cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "40 to 49; deviating from No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "42 No. 3 letter a, however, the transfer of an asset to another domestic permanent establishment of the claimant is harmless if it also serves the beneficiary purposes there"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Beneficiary tangible assets, as well as expansions and expansions 117 (1) The granting of an investment allowance in accordance with Section 4 InvZulG for tangible assets as well as expansions and expansions is only dependent on tax law requirements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An assessment by the economic authorities is not required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "118 (2) According to Section 51 Paragraph 1 No. 2 Letter u Clause 4 EStG, economic goods and expanded or expanded parts of a building are used for research or development, if they are used 1 to gain new scientific or technical knowledge and experience of a general nature (basic research) , 2 for the development of new products or manufacturing processes or 3 for the further development of products or manufacturing processes, insofar as significant changes to these products or processes are developed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For the interpretation of the terms mentioned, Section 234 (2) EStR 1984 applies accordingly with the stipulation that, in deviation from sentences 5 and 6 of this provision, not only physical objects, but also intangible assets (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Software) that are regularly intended for sale to third parties; the storage of data, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Legal information that is to be made available to future customers is still not to be regarded as a new development of products"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "119 (3) The investment allowance can also be considered for assets that are only indirectly used for research or development (cf. Section 234 Paragraph 3 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Section 234 (4) of the EStR applies accordingly to the distinction between harmful and harmless use of economic goods"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 (4) Movable economic goods are only eligible if they are used exclusively for research or development (BFH judgment of 27 4 1978 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "657)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In the case of immovable assets and extensions and extensions to buildings, the preferential treatment can only be considered if the assets or the extended and expanded parts of building 1 are more than 66 2/3 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "serve research or development, or 2 not more than 66 2/3 of a percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": ", but to more than 33 1/3 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "serve for research or development"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Because of the different assessment bases in the cases of numbers 1 and 2, see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "127 Section 234 (5) EStR applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "121 (5) If, during the relevant three-year period, the"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 sentence 2 designated share of use of an immovable asset, the asset remains favored to the extent that the reduced share of use allows a favor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 1: From the time of completion, a building is used as follows: external 250 sqm, internal 750 sqm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The part of the building used by the company is used exclusively for research or development"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "During the three-year period, 250 square meters of the area of \u200b\u200bthe part of the building used by the company will also be used by third parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, the privileged use no longer applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For the new, self-employed part of the building with an area of \u200b\u200b500 square meters, the usage requirement according to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 No. 1 received (see Section 13b Paragraph 2 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 2: From the time of completion, a building is used as follows: external company 250 m2, internal company 750 m2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The part of the building used by the company is used exclusively for research or development"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "During the three-year period, 250 square meters of the area of \u200b\u200bthe part of the building used by the company itself will be transferred to the company's own production area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The part of the building used by the company is only 66 2/3 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "research or development and thus only fulfills the usage requirements in terms of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 No. 2 3 Beneficiaries of intangible assets 122 (1) The economic law prerequisite for the granting of an investment allowance is that the intangible asset is determined and suitable for research or development in the company of the beneficiary exclusively for research or development within the meaning of Section 51 (1) No. 2 letter u sentence 4 double letters bb and cc EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Only those intangible assets that are used for the new development or further development of products or manufacturing processes are benefited, but not those that serve basic research (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "118)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This requirement must be proven by means of a certificate (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "76 to 81)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "123 (2) In addition to the certification that 1 the intangible asset has been acquired and the acquisition costs do not consist of ongoing payments that depend on an uncertain size (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "124), 2 the intangible asset is new and subject to wear and tear (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "125), 3 the seller of the intangible asset is not a person closely related to the purchaser (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "126), 4 the intangible asset remains in the business of the beneficiary for at least three years after its acquisition and does not contain any other than those mentioned in no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "122 serves the purposes mentioned"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "124 (3) Only acquisition costs can be included in the assessment base; the production of intangible assets is not favored"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The acquisition costs must not consist of ongoing payments that are based on uncertain parameters, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "according to future sales or profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Rather, a fixed purchase price must be agreed for the asset, which is to be paid in the form of a one-off payment or payment in installments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "125 (4) An intangible asset is new if the beneficiary has acquired it from the manufacturer and the manufacturer has not yet used this asset by granting usage rights"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If a right (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Patent, copyright) by granting usage rights (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Licenses), every right of use is a new asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "126 (5) Related persons within the meaning of Section 1 (2) AStG can be both legal and natural persons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "These are people who are linked to one another by essential common economic interests"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 1 (2) AStG, this is particularly the case for persons 1 to whom a direct or indirect participation of at least 25 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "exists, 2 who exercise a dominant influence (Section 17 of the German Stock Corporation Act), 3 who have the opportunity outside of the business relationship to influence the terms of the contractual relationship, 4 who have their own interest in generating the other's income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the influence is exercised by the claimant on the other person or by the other person on the claimant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Section 1 (2) AStG is also applicable if a third person exerts influence on the beneficiary and another person as a contractual partner over a substantial participation, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the parent company when acquiring patents between sister companies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For the interpretation of Section 1 (2) AStG, cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "132 of the BMF letter of 23 February 1983 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "218)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "II Assessment of the investment allowance according to \u00a7 4 InvZulG 1 Basis of assessment 127 (1) Insofar as acquisition or production costs are taken into account when assessing the investment allowance, Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 No. 1 in full, 2 the production costs of immovable assets as well as expanded or expanded parts of a building within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 No. 2 to include half and 3 the acquisition costs of intangible assets up to a total of DM 500,000 in the assessment basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "128 (2) If, in one of the preceding financial years, advance payments for acquisition costs or partial production costs were included in the assessment basis, the acquisition or production costs incurred for the corresponding asset or the corresponding expanded or expanded part of the building shall be reduced by the advance payments or partial production costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the tax office determines that part of the production costs were taken into account in full in one of the previous financial years, although only half of the total production costs may be included in the assessment basis (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "127 No. 2), it must correct the assessment basis for the previous financial years (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "87) and to reduce the sum of the half-subsidized manufacturing costs by the partial manufacturing costs reduced by half"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "129 (3) When calculating the investment allowance for down payments on acquisition costs or partial production costs, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "127 No. 2 and 3 accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, the likely conditions in the business year or in the business years of delivery or completion are decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The partial production costs of immovable assets as well as expanded or expanded parts of a building are therefore to be included in the assessment basis to the extent that the final production costs in the fiscal year of completion may be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Advance payments on acquisition costs are favored to the extent that they are likely to be taken into account in the fiscal year or years in which the intangible assets are delivered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "130 (4) The assessment basis for the investment allowance can be determined for each financial year according to the following scheme: Acquisition costs of the movable assets acquired in the financial year Manufacturing costs of the movable and immovable assets completed in the financial year as well as the expanded or expanded parts of buildings within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 No. 1 50 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the production costs of the immovable assets completed in the financial year as well as the developed and expanded parts of buildings within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 No. 2 Acquisition costs of the intangible assets acquired in the financial year, but not more than 500,000 DM, = sum of the acquisition and production costs incurred in the financial year Advance payments on acquisition costs for the assets acquired in the financial year and partial production costs for the assets completed in the financial year as well as expanded or expanded parts of buildings insofar as they have been included in the assessment base in one of the previous financial years as permitted = sum of the purchase and production costs benefited in the financial year.Payments on account of the purchase costs of the movable assets that are purchased in one of the following financial years, partial production costs of the movable and immovable assets as well as the developed ones or extended parts of buildings within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 No. 1 that will be completed in one of the following financial years 50 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the partial production costs of the immovable assets as well as the expanded or expanded parts of buildings within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "120 No. 2 that will be completed in one of the following financial years Advance payments for the acquisition costs of the intangible assets that will be purchased in one of the following financial years, but at most, based on the financial year in which the expected acquisition of the assets for which advance payments have been made, 500,000 DM less the down payments for intangible assets that have not yet been purchased in the fiscal year that are permissible to be included in the assessment base in one of the previous fiscal years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "= Assessment basis 131 (5) Example for determining the assessment basis when changing the planned use of a building and when favoring down payments on the acquisition costs of intangible assets: 1 Construction of a building in 1988 that is 70%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "to serve research or development, but from the time of completion only to 65%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Serves research or development: Partial production costs 1986400000 DM Partial production costs 1987500000 DMRest production costs 1988 100,000 DM Production costs total 1000000 DM2 Acquisition of software in 1987: Down payments 1986600000 DMRest payments 1987200000 DM total acquisition costs 800,000 DM3 Acquisition of a patent in 1988 total DM3,86300 DM3 purchase of a patent total in 1988: Advance payments 1986300000 DMDM finally 50 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of the production costs of the building 500,000 DM, acquisition costs of the software 1987500,000 DM, acquisition costs of the patent 1988500,000 DM assessment basis up to and including"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "1988 a total of 1,500,000 DM assessment base 198619871988- in DM -50%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the production costs of the building + 500,000 acquisition costs for- software (maximum limit) + 500,000- patent (maximum limit) + 500,000 advance payments for- software (maximum limit) + 500,000 - 500,000 - patent + 300,000 + 200,000 - 500,000 partial production costs of the building + 400,000 + 500,000 - 450,000+ 1,200,000 + 700,000+ 50,000 correction of the assessment base due to change in use- 200,000 - 250,000 Final assessment base + 1,000,000 + 450,000+ 500002 Amount of the investment allowance 132 The investment allowance is 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the acquisition or manufacturing costs of the assets acquired or manufactured in the fiscal year and the manufacturing costs of the expansions and extensions completed in the fiscal year, insofar as the acquisition or manufacturing costs do not exceed the amount of 500,000 DM, and 75%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the acquisition or production costs exceeding this amount (Section 4 (1) sentence 3 InvZulG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For the calculation of the increased investment allowance, the amount of the total subsidized acquisition or production costs of the assets acquired or manufactured in the financial year is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For the business year of acquisition or manufacture, the increased tax base is reduced if it has already been used up in the previous business years through advance payments on acquisition costs or through partial production costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Advance payments or partial production costs for investments in the following financial years can also receive increased benefits in the financial year of the advance payment or partial production within the framework of the annual maximum"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example: In 1986 advance payments of 300,000 DM are made for items delivered in 1987 (A) with acquisition costs of 400,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In 1987 the remainder of DM 100,000 is paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In addition, in 1987 economic goods (B) with acquisition costs of DM 150,000 were delivered and down payments of 600,000 DM were made for economic goods (C) delivered in 1988 with acquisition costs of 800,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In 1988 the remainder of DM 200,000 is paid on delivery"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The down payments in 1988 for goods delivered in 1989 (D) amount to DM 100,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Calculation: Investment allowance 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "from 75 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "From 1986 down payments for goods delivered in 1987 (A) 300,000 DM 300,000 DM-1987 acquisition costs (A) 400,000 DM down payments 300,000 DM 100,000 DM acquisition costs (B) 150,000 DM 100,000 DM50000 DM Down payments for goods delivered in 1988 (C) 600,000 DM500,000 DM100,000 DM700000 DM150000 DM-1988 acquisition costs (C) Down payments 600,000 DM-200,000 DM Down payments for goods delivered in 1989 (D) 100,000 DM 100,000 DM-100,000 DM 200,000 DMC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Investment allowance for certain investments in the field of energy generation and distribution according to \u00a7 4a InvZulG I overview 133 or heat recovery system within the meaning of Section 4a (3) InvZulG is particularly suitable for saving energy"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This also includes the fact that the technical system is related to the construction or expansion of one of the energy generation or energy distribution systems specified in Section 4a Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 1 InvZulG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This requirement must be proven by means of a certificate (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "76 to 81)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "134 (2) In addition to the certificate, the tax law prerequisites include the following: 1 The technical systems specified in the certificate - with the exception of the systems within the meaning of Section 4a Paragraph 3 InvZulG - are independent assets or expanded or newly manufactured parts of an immovable asset or a district heating network are (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "135 to 137), 2 the expenses for the purchased or manufactured assets, for the expanded or newly manufactured parts as well as for systems within the meaning of Section 4a (3) InvZulG are acquisition or manufacturing costs (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "138), 3 the purchased or manufactured assets, the expanded or newly manufactured parts and the systems within the meaning of Section 4a Paragraph 3 InvZulG remain in the taxpayer's business for at least three years after their acquisition or manufacture (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "139) and 4 the systems referred to in Section 4a (3) InvZulG are used exclusively to generate electricity or heat or are used for waste heat recovery during the three-year remaining period (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "140)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "II Beneficial investments according to \u00a7 4a InvZulG 1 Beneficial assets, expanded or newly manufactured parts and systems 135 Newly manufactured parts of immovable assets, expanded or newly manufactured parts of district heating networks or solar, wind power or heat recovery systems"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The tax office determines whether there is an independent asset or an expanded or newly manufactured part of an immovable asset or a district heating network"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "136 (2) The preferential treatment of district heating networks includes both the expansion of a district heating network planned as a single economic asset and the expansion and strengthening of an existing network"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The district heating network technically includes the distribution systems up to the connection to the heating system of the building, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "including the branch line into the building and the transfer station for the building with all necessary fittings, valves and heat exchangers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For other heat distribution systems, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For industrial process steam networks, an investment allowance can only be considered as a dependent part of a beneficiary asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "137 (3) In the case of solar, wind power and heat recovery systems, it is irrelevant whether they are independent economic goods or dependent parts of a building or operating equipment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The delimitation of the system made in the certification process is binding for the tax office (see BFH judgment of 9 12 1982 - BStBl 1983 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "417)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The tax office therefore only has to check whether the system actually constructed is identical to the one specified in the certificate and actually serves the beneficiary purposes (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "139)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Delimitation of production costs 138 Section 4a InvZulG is only considered for production costs and for certain subsequent production costs, apart from acquisition costs (for the delimitation see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "61 to 63 and 67)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Expenses for a heat pump as part of a heating system or for a solar or heat recovery system are only manufacturing costs if they were incurred during the manufacture of a building or operating equipment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, an existing heating system is supplemented by the installation of a solar, heat pump or heat recovery system or parts of an existing heating system are replaced, the expenses for the installation are maintenance expenses (cf. Section 157 Paragraph 1 EStR) and are therefore not favored"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 Prerequisites for Remaining and Use 139 (1) The investment allowance can only be granted for assets, expanded or newly manufactured parts or systems that remain in the taxpayer's business for at least three years after their acquisition or manufacture and serve the beneficiary purposes there during this period (BFH judgment of 25 October 1985 - BStBl 1986 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "150)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Only the transfer to another permanent establishment of the same taxpayer is harmless - unlike in the cases of Section 1 (3) No. 1 InvZulG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "40 to 49 140 (2) Solar and wind power systems as well as systems for heat recovery must be used during the three-year period, contrary to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "139 serve exclusively to generate electricity or heat or are used exclusively to recover waste heat"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the certification for a system is limited to the parts of a technical system that can only be used for the purposes benefited from, sentence 1 only applies to this part"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Investment allowance for investments in Berlin (West) according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG I Overview 141 (1) An investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG is granted 1 for movable assets (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "22 to 31), 2 for immovable assets that are buildings, parts of buildings, condominiums or rooms that are partially owned (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "32), 3 for the expansion and expansion of immovable assets designated under number 2 (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "34) and 4 for other subsequent manufacturing work on immovable assets designated under number 2 (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "152)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Subsequent manufacturing work on movable assets (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "26) are not favored"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "142 (2) The investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG is generally 10% for movable assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of acquisition or production costs and for preferential immovable assets 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the manufacturing costs; An increased investment allowance is granted for assets that serve certain privileged purposes (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "143 (3) The granting of an investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG is only dependent on tax law requirements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An assessment by the economic authorities is not required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "144 (4) Notwithstanding no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "50 not to be included in a special register"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "II Basic funding 1 Movable economic goods a) General 145 An investment allowance can be considered for movable economic goods for the purchase and manufacture"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "b) Passenger vehicles 146 (1) An investment allowance can only be granted for passenger vehicles if, at least three years after their acquisition or manufacture in the company's own commercial operation, they are used exclusively 1 to transport people for a fee or 2 are rented to self-drivers or 3 are used for driving school purposes (Section 19 (2) sentences 1 and 2 BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An investment allowance cannot be considered for passenger vehicles that are used as a freelance driver for driving school purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For passenger vehicles that are rented to self-drivers (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "149), an investment allowance must also be granted if the passenger vehicles are used by the tenants in whole or in part for private purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "147 (2) Use for the beneficiary purposes also exists insofar as passenger vehicles are used to the usual extent for journeys that are caused by the beneficiary use (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "146 sentence 1) are absolutely necessary (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Trips to the company, to refueling, to the workshop, to the T\u00dcV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, use in addition to those mentioned in paragraph"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "146 is detrimental to other operational purposes and leads to the refusal of the investment allowance (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Rental to third parties - except for self-drivers, see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "149 - or transfer to third parties, even if the third party uses the passenger vehicle in its commercial operation for the beneficiary purposes)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Use for own private purposes in addition to use exclusively for the beneficiary operational purposes is, however, harmless if it exceeds the limit of 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of the total usage (BFH judgment of 31 July 1981 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "772)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 1: A passenger vehicle becomes 87 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "for driving school purposes, to 4 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "for trips to refuel, to the workshop and to the T\u00dcV and to 9%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "used by the owner of the driving school (tradesman) for their own private purposes (shopping trips, visiting trips, vacation trips)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An investment allowance can be granted for the passenger car"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 2: Situation as in Example 1 The owner of the driving school does not use the car for his own private purposes, but leaves it to an employed driving instructor (occasionally, for a fee or free of charge) for his private purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The proportion of use by the driving instructor is 9%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The transfer to the employee is indeed operational; but it does not belong to the favored operational purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An investment allowance cannot be granted for the passenger car"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 3: A passenger vehicle becomes 87 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "for rent to self-drivers, to 4 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "to trips to refuel, to the workshop and to the T\u00dcV and to 9 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "used by the owner of the company for their own private purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The tenants also include those who use the passenger vehicle in whole or in part for private purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Private use by tenants is not harmful (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "146)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An investment allowance can be granted for the passenger car"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "148 (3) The distinction between passenger vehicles and other motor vehicles is for the purposes of the investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG according to the definition in \u00a7 10 paragraph 2 of the Motor Vehicle Tax Act 1972 in the version valid until 1978 (BStBl 1972 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "551) (see BFH rulings of 23 August 1966 - BStBl 1967 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "66 and from 1 7 1977 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "864)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "According to this, passenger vehicles are vehicles which, according to their design and equipment, are suitable and intended for the transport of no more than seven people (including the driver); this also applies if goods are transported in the passenger vehicle or in a trailer carried by it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A motor vehicle that, after its construction, is also set up and intended to transport goods in addition to people, either or at the same time, is not to be regarded as a passenger vehicle if the usable area for transporting goods is greater than 2 1/2 square meters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The usable area also includes the area that is created by removing seats, but not the area that is set up and intended for the transport of luggage outside the car body"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether the vehicle is actually used to transport people or whether it is used exclusively or partially for other purposes; The only decisive factor is the objective structural condition of the motor vehicle"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Is a usable area for the transport of goods created by removing seats or is a conversion z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "made for use as a workshop vehicle, so that the vehicle can objectively no longer be used for passenger transport, but only for the transport of goods or as a mobile workshop, it is no longer a passenger vehicle"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, the transformation must be permanent; this is only the case if the restoration of the previous state would involve a not inconsiderable amount of work and costs (BFH judgment of 1 7 1977 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "864)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Mobile homes (camper vans) are to be regarded as passenger vehicles"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Ambulance vehicles that are exempt from vehicle tax are not passenger vehicles within the meaning of Section 19 (2) sentence 2 BerlinFG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "149 (4) The requirement \"in one's own commercial operation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "rented to self-drivers \"is to be regarded as fulfilled if the requirements of the regulation on the supervision of passenger cars and motorcycles to be rented commercially to self-drivers of 4 4 1955 (Federal Law Gazette I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "186) in the version of the amending ordinance of 7 July 1960 (Federal Law Gazette I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "485) and the amending ordinance of 21 July 1969 (Federal Law Gazette I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "875) are given"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "According to this ordinance, rental to self-drivers exists if a motor vehicle is rented commercially without providing a driver and this activity has been reported in writing to the supervisory authority"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The rental to self-drivers can also take place within the framework of a commercial enterprise that has other activities as its subject"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, the prerequisite for the preferential treatment is that the rental business has the characteristics of a commercial enterprise"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "No rental \"in your own commercial operation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "to self-drivers \"occurs when a GmbH gives its managing directors or shareholders a car for a fee that does not cover cost (BFH judgment of 11 10 1970 - BStBl 1971 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "173)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "150 (5) For passenger vehicles rented out by leasing companies, an investment allowance is not eligible because they are usually long-term rentals; Long-term rental can be assumed in particular if the passenger vehicle is registered for the tenant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Buildings, extensions and extensions, other subsequent production work a) Company building 151 (1) An investment allowance is only paid for those in No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "141 No. 2 to 4 designated immovable economic goods, extensions and extensions as well as other subsequent production work into consideration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Other immovable assets, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Courtyard fortifications, fences, roads, bridges, rainwater catchment systems are not favored (BFH rulings of 13 2 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "320 and from 14 10 1977 - BStBl 1978 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "163)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "152 (2) Other subsequent production work within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "141 No. 4 exists when buildings are increased in substance, changed in their essence or considerably improved beyond their previous condition and the costs incurred are manufacturing costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Because of the delimitation of the subsidized production costs from the non-subsidized maintenance costs for company property, see Section 24 in conjunction with Section 157 EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The subsequent production work does not include all measures that serve to complete the assets (cf. also No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "61 last sentence)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In the case of subsequent construction work on a building on third-party land and on tenant installations and tenant conversions, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "33 accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "153 (3) The prerequisite for the granting of an investment allowance is that a) the buildings, parts of buildings, condominiums and partially owned rooms (preferential immovable assets) are built in West Berlin and the requirements of Section 14 (2) sentence 1 no.2 A) BerlinFG, b) the extensions or extensions (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "34) are carried out on beneficiary immovable assets located in Berlin (West) and the expanded or newly manufactured parts meet the requirements of Section 14 Paragraph 2 Sentence 1 No. 2 Letter a or Paragraph 4 BerlinFG, c) the other subsequent production work on in Berlin ( West) beneficiary immovable assets are made and these immovable assets meet the requirements of Section 14 Paragraph 2 Sentence 1 No. 2 Letter a or Paragraph 4 BerlinFG (Section 19 Paragraph 2 last sentence BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "154 (4) The beneficiary immovable assets and the expansions and extensions of beneficiary immovable assets must accordingly, unless the requirements of Section 14 (4) BerlinFG are met (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "167 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "), in their own commercial operation at least three years after their production to more than 80%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "directly serve one or more or the following beneficial purposes: 1 the production or processing of economic goods intended for sale or the restoration of economic goods or the generation of energy or heat or 2 research or development within the meaning of Section 51 Paragraph 1 No. 2 Letter u Clause 4 EStG or 3 of the management or administration or the storage of inventories in connection with the production or processing of economic goods intended for sale, the restoration of economic goods, the generation of energy or heat or research or development"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In the case of other subsequent production work, the beneficiary immovable assets on which the production work has been carried out must meet these requirements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "155 (5) When assessing whether the 80%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "-The limit of the beneficiary use is exceeded, is based on the individual asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if a building consists of several independent assets (Section 13b (2) EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "156 (6) Beneficiary immovable assets as well as expansions and extensions of beneficiary immovable assets generally serve for more than 80 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the beneficiary purposes if the area of \u200b\u200bthe rooms serving these purposes is more than 80 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of the total usable area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If there are significant deviations in the height of the storey, the 80 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "-Boundary not to be based on the usable area, but on the enclosed space"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A significant deviation in the storey height is to be assumed if it is at least 50 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "amounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If rooms are used for both privileged and non-privileged purposes, the individual room, depending on which use predominates in it, is either wholly assigned to the privileged or the non-privileged rooms"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The floor space of stairwells that are not located within rooms is not taken into account when calculating the total usable area as well as when calculating the floor area of \u200b\u200bthe rooms serving the preferred purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "157 (7) Design offices, laboratories and similar rooms or buildings used in connection with the beneficiary purposes also directly serve the beneficiary purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to sanitary facilities, lounges, canteens, garages and similar rooms and buildings that are predominantly used by people who work in favored areas of operation (Section 14 (2) sentence 1 no.2 letter a double letter aa to ee BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "158 (8) Manufacturing within the meaning of Section 14 Paragraph 2 Clause 1 No. 2 Letter a Double Letter aa BerlinFG is understood to mean the manual or industrial production of material economic goods (manufacture); Original production, trade and services do not belong to production in this sense (see BFH judgment of 6 8 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "772)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Production includes all areas, the expenditure of which must be recognized as production costs (BFH judgment of 27 3 1973 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "674)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "159 (9) Processing within the meaning of Section 14 (2) sentence 1 no.2 letter a double letter bb BerlinFG does not exist if stored economic goods are merely shoveled, turned over, ventilated or similarly treated in the simplest way to avoid spoilage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "160 (10) Restoration of assets within the meaning of Section 14 Paragraph 2 Clause 1 No. 2 Letter a Double Letter cc BerlinFG is a process through which a substantial or functional impairment of an asset is eliminated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This is not the case when lubricating machines, washing vehicles, washing and cleaning used laundry and similar processes (see BFH judgment of 16 5 1957 - BStBl III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "228)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Buildings, the main purpose of which is to shelter vehicles and protect them against the effects of the weather (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Garages), are not used for the restoration of economic goods, even if the usual maintenance work and minor repairs are carried out in them"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If major repairs and thorough overhauls are carried out in such a building at the same time, it is one of the beneficiary buildings"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "161 (11) Because of the terms research and development within the meaning of Section 14 (2) sentence 1 no.2 letter a double letter dd BerlinFG, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "118 pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "162 (12) Beneficiary immovable assets that serve the management or administration or the storage of inventories meet the requirements of Section 14 (2) sentence 1 no.2 letter a double letter ee BerlinFG only if the management, administration or storage of inventories is functionally related to one or more of the activities described in Section 14 (2) sentence 1 no.2 letter a double letters aa to dd BerlinFG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "163 (13) In the case of management and administration, these must be directly prompted by the beneficiary activities; an indirect connection is not sufficient"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for immediate initiation is always present if and to the extent that work / processes are carried out, the expenditure of which must be recognized as production costs (see Section 33 (2) sentence 1 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, the prerequisite for the direct initiation by the beneficiary activities does not exist if and to the extent that work / processes are carried out, the expenses of which must be recognized as sales costs (see Section 33 Paragraph 2 Clause 4 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "164 (14) In the case of work / processes, the expenses of which can be included in the production costs (cf. Section 33 Paragraph 2 Clause 2 and 3 EStR), it must always be checked - regardless of whether this option is used for income taxes - whether there is still a direct there is a functional connection with one of the beneficiary activities; only if this is the case do the requirements of Section 14 (2) sentence 1 no.2 letter a double letter ee BerlinFG apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 1: The operational accounting for the cost centers in the production area is housed in one room"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The expenses for the operational accounting as part of the accounting can be included in the production costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The expenses are caused by favored activities (production of assets intended for sale); there is a direct functional connection with these activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The room is to be assigned to the beneficiary rooms"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 2: A part of the accounting of a manufacturing company is housed in a room"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The employees are 60 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of their working hours with work in the accounts receivable area and 40%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of their working hours working in the accounts payable area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The expenses for the accounts receivable area are directly functionally related to sales; they are not caused by favored activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The expenses that arise in the accounts payable area can be directly attributable to the beneficiary activities (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Booking of invoices and payment transactions for the delivery of production material) as well as directly by the sales department (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Posting of invoices and payment transactions for shipping costs for finished products)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A breakdown of these costs is unnecessary in the example because 60%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of the entire working time is devoted to work in the accounts receivable area and is therefore not directly functionally related to beneficiary activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The fact that the expenses attributable to sales were caused indirectly by a favored activity (production of economic goods intended for sale) is not sufficient"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The room is to be assigned to the non-favored rooms"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "165 (15) Beneficiary immovable assets that are used to store inventories meet the requirements of Section 14 Paragraph 2 Clause 1 No. 2 Letter a, Double Letter ee BerlinFG, even if the stored inventories are self-made finished products"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "166 (16) A connection with the beneficiary activities does not presuppose that there is a spatial connection between the management, administration or storage of stocks and the beneficiary activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The connection is therefore z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the beneficiary maintains a permanent establishment in Berlin (West) in which a production facility, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "is carried out, and the raw material store or the finished goods store or the management is spatially remote from it in Berlin (West)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "b) Modernization measures on hotel buildings 167 (1) An investment allowance can also be made for modernization measures on buildings in West Berlin if the buildings in a hotel or restaurant business are mainly used for accommodation at least three years after the completion of the subsequent production work (\u00a7 19 para 2 sentence 4 in conjunction with \u00a7 14 para 4 BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "168 (2) The concept of modernization within the meaning of Section 14 (4) BerlinFG presupposes that the modernization measures are carried out on an existing hotel or restaurant building; the building must have served the beneficiary purposes or one of the beneficiary purposes before the construction work is carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The modernization measures are only favored if they lead to manufacturing costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether extensions or expansions (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "34) or other subsequent production work (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "152) are carried out insofar as the measures create or transform facilities or facilities within the meaning of Section 14 (4) BerlinFG; Section 158 (1) and (6) EStR 1981 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The favored modernization measures can also be carried out on immovable assets that are parts of buildings, condominiums or partially owned rooms"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "It is not necessary that the buildings etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "serve the beneficiary purposes in the beneficiary's own business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "169 (3) For the assessment of whether a building will be used primarily for accommodation for at least three years after the modernization measures in a hotel or restaurant business have been completed, the ratio of the usable area in the next three years is to be used as a standard for allocation (cf. Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "156)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "170 158 para 2 EStR 1981)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 Prerequisites for whereabouts and use a) Movable assets aa) General 171 (1) Only movable assets that are considered to be fixed assets at least three years (eight years for ships) after their acquisition or manufacture are eligible for the investment allowance under Section 19 BerlinFG Remain in an establishment located in West Berlin (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "40 to 49)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for remaining is - in deviation from No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "42 46 and 48 - also fulfilled if a beneficiary movable asset is transferred within three (eight) years after its acquisition or manufacture 1 by sale to the fixed assets of a permanent establishment located in Berlin (West) of another (BFH judgment of 18 2 1965 - BStBl III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "362) or 2 is transferred to another permanent establishment in Berlin (West) or 3 is used by renting or leasing another permanent establishment located in Berlin (West) (BFH judgment of 6 5 1977 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "592)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Legal entities under public law only have a permanent establishment insofar as they maintain a business of a commercial nature (Section 4 KStG, Section 5 KStR, BFH judgment of 21 2 1986 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "493), and corporation taxpayers within the meaning of Section 1 Paragraph 1 No. 3 to 5 KStG only insofar as they generate income within the meaning of Section 2 Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 3 EStG, and corporations, associations of persons and estates that are personally exempt from corporation tax (Section 5 Paragraph 1 KStG) only insofar as they have an economic business with income within the meaning of Section 2 Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 3 EStG - even if this is a purpose-built business (Sections 65 to 68 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "172 (2) Because of the use of passenger vehicles in one's own commercial operation for the beneficiary purposes, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "146 147 and 149 pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In the event that a subsidized passenger vehicle is sold before the end of the period of stay and use, the requirement of three years of service in one's own commercial operation is also fulfilled if the buyer continues to use the passenger vehicle for the beneficiary purposes in his own commercial operation up to the end of the three-year period (BFH judgment of 31 July 1981 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "772)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "173 (3) Renting, leasing or leasing out movable assets for purposes of private use is harmful"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Because of the exception for passenger vehicles that are rented to self-drivers, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "146 referenced"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "bb) Economic goods which, by their nature, can also be used outside of a permanent establishment (excluding inland vessels) 174 (1) For means of transport - with the exception of inland vessels (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "178 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": ") - is No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "113 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For vehicle trailers that are registered in accordance with Section 1 Paragraph 1 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "745; StZBl Bln S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "637) are exempt from vehicle tax, proof of the existence of the remaining requirements must be kept in the control book (Section 1 Paragraph 3 Clause 1 of the Ordinance) (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "16 of the decree of the Senator for Finances Berlin of 15 3 1978 - StZBl Bln"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "638 BFH judgment of 27 June 1984 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "854)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "175 (2) In the case of construction equipment, the requirement of three years of residence is to be considered as fulfilled if it is only used within Berlin (West) or only briefly outside of Berlin (West)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "A short-term assignment in this sense is only given if all assignments outside of Berlin (West) together do not last more than 5 months in each year of the three-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "176 (3) In the case of an exhibition bus mainly used outside of Berlin (West), the spatial and temporal connection to the Berlin operating facility must be affirmed if the bus from this operating site is used to advertise the Berlin economy (BFH judgment of 20 11 1970 - BStBl 1971 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "155)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "177 (4) For other than those mentioned in paragraph"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "174 to 176 designated assets, which by their nature are not only intended to remain physically in a permanent establishment, short-term use outside of Berlin (West) is harmless"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Short-term use is when the asset is used for no more than 1 month outside of Berlin (West) in each year of the three-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "cc) Inland navigation vessels 178 (1) If an inland shipping company does not have an operating facility in Berlin (West) or in the rest of Germany (Section 12 AO), the requirement of belonging to the fixed assets of an operating facility located in Berlin (West) applies to an inland navigation vessel fulfilled if the inland waterway vessel is entered in the shipping register of the Charlottenburg District Court with its home town of Berlin and is mainly used in Berlin traffic in the relevant eight-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "179 (2) An inland waterway vessel is mainly used in Berlin traffic if more than half of its operating days are spent on Berlin journeys in the eight years following its acquisition or manufacture"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "180 (3) A trip to Berlin is given if the inland vessel 1 operates on West Berlin waters or 2 operates between Berlin (West) and the rest of the country or between Berlin (West) and abroad and a) there is an empty trip to accommodate for Berlin-specific charge (Berlin charge) or to return to Berlin (West) takes place, or b) has only accepted Berlin charge or c) if other than Berlin charge has also been accepted, the Berlin charge is either at least 25 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": ", the permissible carrying capacity of the inland waterway vessel or 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of the hold of the inland waterway vessel"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Berlin loads are goods that are transported from Berlin (West) or to Berlin (West)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "181 (4) A trip to Berlin begins 1 in the case of paragraph 3 No. 2 letter a at the beginning of the day on which the inland waterway vessel departs; 2 in the case of paragraph 3 no.2 letter b with the beginning of the day on which the Berlin summons begins or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the deletion of another harmful cargo is terminated; 3 in the case of paragraph 3 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Limit is reached or exceeded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "(5) A trip to Berlin ends 1 in the case of paragraph 3 No. 2 letter a at the end of the day on which the port of destination is reached; 2 in the case of Paragraph 3 No. 2 Letter b at the end of the day on which the unloading of the Berlin cargo is ended or the picking up of a harmful cargo begins; 3 in the case of paragraph 3 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Limit is undershot, deletion of this part is ended"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "183 (6) Operating days are the days on which the inland waterway vessel sails, is loaded or unloaded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The operating days also include the days on which a journey, loading or unloading is interrupted, but no more than 7 days"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The same goes for days when the ship is waiting for a new load"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "184 (7) The days on which a barge makes trips to Berlin are determined by paragraphs 3 to 5"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the interruption of trips to Berlin and the waiting times between two trips to Berlin, paragraph 6 sentences 2 and 3 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "185 (8) For reasons of simplification, it can be assumed that the inland waterway vessel was mainly used in Berlin traffic in one year if it was in use for at least 136 days for Berlin journeys"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "b) Immovable assets 186 (1) An investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG is only granted for preferential immovable assets, for extensions and extensions and other subsequent production work on preferential immovable assets, if they are at least three years after their production or termination to the fixed assets of the permanent establishment of the Eligible persons in Berlin (West) belong (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "40 42 and 44 to 49)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "187 (2) The investment allowance is 20 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the manufacturing costs; it increases to 25 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the production costs if the requirements of Section 19 (1) sentence 4 no.2 BerlinFG are met (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "214)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the application for a building permit was submitted before 1 4 1985, the investment allowance is 15%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "20 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the manufacturing costs; If an application for a building permit is not required under building law, the construction work begins in its place (see Section 31, Paragraph 19 BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "188 (3) For preferential immovable assets an investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG is only granted if the beneficiary immovable assets are more than 80% in their own commercial enterprise at least three years after their production"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "directly serve the purposes specified in Section 14 Paragraph 2 Sentence 1 No. 2 Letter a BerlinFG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG is only granted for expansions and extensions to beneficiary immovable assets if the expanded or newly manufactured parts meet the requirements of \u00a7 14 Paragraph 2 Sentence 1 No. 2 Letter a or Paragraph 4 BerlinFG at least three years after their manufacture"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For other subsequent production work on preferential immovable assets, an investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG is only granted if the beneficiary immovable asset on which the subsequent production work has been carried out meets the requirements of \u00a7 14 Paragraph 2 Clause 1 at least three years after the completion of the subsequent production work No. 2 letter a or paragraph 4 BerlinFG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "189 (4) Renting or leasing and selling the beneficiary immovable property before the end of the three-year period of stay and use is detrimental, even if the tenant or leaseholder or the purchaser of the immovable property in his own commercial operation is in accordance with Section 14 (2) Sentence 1 no.2 letter a BerlinFG uses designated beneficial purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Sentence 1 does not apply to investment grants for modernization measures on hotel buildings within the meaning of Section 14 (4) BerlinFG (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "168)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "190 (5) If the actual use of a beneficiary immovable asset changes during the relevant three-year period (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "188) in such a way that the economic good is no longer or partially no longer used for internal purposes or for the beneficiary internal purposes, the requirements for the investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG do not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, the economic asset continues to be favored if and to the extent that the reduced use for the favored corporate purposes permits this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 1: From the time of completion, a building is used as follows: external 250 sqm, internal 750 sqm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The part of the building used by the company is used exclusively for the production of certain assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "During the three-year period, 250 square meters of the area of \u200b\u200bthe part of the building used by the company will also be used by third parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, the investment allowance must be reclaimed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For the remaining self-used building part of 500 square meters, which will also be used exclusively for production in the future, the prerequisite for use remains because this asset (see Section 13b Paragraph 2 EStR) continues to be more than 80 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "directly serves the beneficiary purposes (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "155)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 2: From the time of completion, a building is used as follows: external company 250 m2, internal company 750 m2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The part of the building used by the company is used exclusively for research or development"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "During the three-year period, 250 square meters of the area of \u200b\u200bthe part of the building used by the company itself will be transferred to the company's own production area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The part of the building used by the company is no longer used for more than 80 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of research or development, but still to more than 80 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the beneficiary purposes as a whole (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "156)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "There is therefore only an investment allowance of 20% for the entire part of the building used by the company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "of the production costs (\u00a7 19 Paragraph 1 Sentence 3 No. 2 BerlinFG) and no longer of 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the production costs (Section 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 2 BerlinFG); the excess amount (5%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the beneficiary manufacturing costs) is to be reclaimed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example 3: From the time of completion on, a building is used as follows: external 250 sqm, internal 750 sqm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The part of the building, which is used by the company itself, has 650 square meters (866 BC)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": ") the production for the sale of certain economic goods and the administration in connection with this beneficiary activity as well as with 100 square meters of the sales and administration in connection with this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "During the three-year period, another 100 square meters of the area of \u200b\u200bthe part of the building used by the company will be taken over into the sales department"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The part of the building used by the company is only used with 550 square meters (733 BC)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "), so no more than 80 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the beneficiary activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The investment allowance must be reclaimed in full"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "III Special conditions for the increased investment allowance for movable assets 1 The 25 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "increased investment allowance a) Manufacturing industry - except construction industry - aa) Delimitation 191 (1) The delimitation of the construction industry from other manufacturing industries is to be carried out as closely as possible to the systematic directory of economic sectors published by the Federal Statistical Office (BFH rulings of 14 1 1975 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "392 and p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "406 and from 8 4 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "410)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The principles of these judgments apply accordingly to the delimitation of the manufacturing industry from the other economic sectors (BFH judgments of 25 6 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "612, from 10 12 1976 - BStBl II 1977 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "233 and from 2 5 1980 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "732)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "192 (2) A legal claim to the granting of an increased investment allowance cannot be derived from the classification of a company in a trade class of Department 2 of the Systematic Directory of Economic Branches by the State Statistical Office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The final decision as to whether a company can be assigned to the manufacturing industry is made by the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "This applies above all if the classification is in obvious contradiction to the actual conditions of the company or if the company of the beneficiary is undergoing structural change, but also if the trade carried out is not yet listed in the systematic directory"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "193 (3) If a company carries out a mixed activity, the requirement of manufacturing is only fulfilled if the manufacturing activity predominates, taking into account all the establishments belonging to the company (BFH judgment of 23 September 1983 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "778)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the beneficiary only has one permanent establishment in Berlin (West), sentence 1 applies accordingly to the permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the business of the beneficiary includes both business premises in Berlin (West) and outside of Berlin (West), sentence 1 shall apply with the proviso that all business premises located in Berlin (West) are to be used; However, it is harmless if the business of the beneficiary does not belong in its entirety to the manufacturing industry (BFH judgment of 10 12 1976 - BStBl II 1977 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "233)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "194 (4) The question of whether the manufacturing activity predominates in a company in which a mixed activity is carried out must be decided according to the circumstances of the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In this context, the sales, the invested capital, the wages or a combination of all or some of these characteristics can be considered as distinguishing features (BFH judgment of 23 7 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "705)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "bb) Manufacturing 195 (1) Because of the term \"manufacturing\", reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "158 pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Whether an asset is used for production can only be judged on the basis of the function of the respective asset in the company (the permanent establishment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "196 (2) Since indirect service is sufficient for production, the circle of assets with increased privileges cannot be narrowly drawn"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, not only the machinery used for production, but also other movable assets used in the production area, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Electric carts, forklifts, conveyor belts, lifting platforms, unloading devices, cupboards and shelves for storing the material to be processed, drawing and duplicating devices in the design office, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": ", but also a drinks machine for the employees working in production, which is mainly used by them (BFH rulings of 27 3 1973 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "674 and from 11 10 1973 - BStBl II 1974 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "43)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The production is also used for assets, the acquisition or production costs of which are included as depreciation in the production overheads of the products manufactured by the processing company (BFH judgment of 29 3 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "409)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Furthermore, the production of assets that produce goods for immediate delivery to the end user, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "a soft ice cream machine in a bakery, a meat grinder in a butcher shop"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Economic goods that are used in administration or management are used for production if the administration or management concerns the production area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "197 (3) Production does not include sales, administration and management, insofar as they serve sales (BFH judgment of 29 3 1976 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "409)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Economic goods that are used directly or indirectly for distribution are not given higher discounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Distribution also includes the packaging of the manufactured goods if it is intended to make the goods more transportable for delivery to the customer or to protect them from damage, soiling, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "(Outer packaging)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The production area, on the other hand, includes the costs of packaging, which is used to make the product salable (inner packaging)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Inner packaging is only used if this is necessary from the point of view of the product, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Toothpaste in tubes, food in cans, instant coffee in glasses, margarine in cups, bread or sausage slices in plastic film; The packaging machines used for this are still used for production (BFH judgments of 3 3 1978 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "412, 413)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "198 (4) If an asset is used in a manufacturing company (a permanent establishment) not only in the production area but also in other areas of the company, it is only more favorably priced if it is primarily used for production (BFH judgment of 27th 1973 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "674)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The same applies if an economic good is used primarily for production as well as other more favored purposes (generation of energy or heat, research or development) (BFH judgment of 17 12 1976 - BStBl II 1977 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "234)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "cc) Data processing 199 (1) Data processing within the meaning of Section 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 1 Letter a Double Letter aa and bb BerlinFG is the evaluation of input data on data processing systems for the client or for the utilization of the results in one's own company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The mere creation of data carriers (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Punched tape, magnetic tapes, magnetic cards, floppy disks), and the mere printing of data"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "200 (2) The beneficiary assets must be used directly for data processing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Economic goods that are only used indirectly for data processing (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Motor vehicles, office equipment, cupboards and shelves for storing magnetic tapes etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": ", Duplicators) are not more favored"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "201 (3) Assets that are used directly for data processing in a manufacturing company are more favored regardless of the area in which they are used in such a company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "b) Energy sector 202 (1) The increased investment allowance is also granted for wear-and-tear movable assets that are used directly or indirectly to generate energy or heat or directly for data processing in a company in the energy industry, including district heating plants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The restriction of the preferential treatment to assets that are used to generate energy or heat corresponds to the limitation of the preferential treatment in manufacturing to assets that are used for production"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "According to this, in the energy industry, including district heating plants, the increased investment allowance is only eligible for assets that are used directly for data processing and for generation plants including investments in the high and medium voltage network (electrical energy) or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "in the high and medium pressure network (gas), but not for investments in the low voltage network, in the low pressure network, in the pipeline network of the district heating plants including the connections of the consumers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Expenses for investments in the networks are only benefited if they are not related to subsequent production costs (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "26) or maintenance costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, the planned expansion of a district heating network planned as a uniform asset is - even if it takes place in stages over several years - to be regarded as the production of a uniform asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "203 (2) Because of the term data processing, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "199 pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Economic goods that are used directly for data processing in a company in the energy industry, including district heating plants, are eligible for increased allowances regardless of whether they are used in the field of energy or heat generation or in other operational areas; Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "200 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "c) Service trades aa) Delimitation 204 The service trades include commercial enterprises in which the focus of economic activity is not on the execution of deliveries, including works deliveries, but on the execution of other services"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The systematic directory of the economic sectors published by the Federal Statistical Office can be used as an aid to distinguish the service industry from the other economic sectors"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "In general, the beneficiaries are the businesses in the branches of the economy listed in sections 5 (transport and communication), 6 (credit institutions and insurance companies) and 7 (services provided by companies and professions)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The service industry, however, only includes companies whose activities are aimed at generating income from commercial operations within the meaning of Section 15 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Businesses in the trade (section 4 of the directory) do not belong to the service industry in this sense"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "bb) Data processing 205 For the term data processing and for the delimitation of the beneficiary assets, no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "199 and 200 respectively"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "cc) Distance selling orientation 206 (1) For the granting of the increased investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 1 Letter a, double letter cc BerlinFG, the prerequisite is that the turnover of the business (the permanent establishment) in Berlin (West) is in the calendar year of acquisition or manufacture the beneficiary assets and in the two following calendar years mainly other services to clients outside of Berlin (West)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If the turnover of the business (the permanent establishment) in Berlin (West) in the calendar year of the acquisition or production of the beneficiary assets does not mainly relate to other services to clients outside of Berlin (West) or if the 50 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "- If the limit is not exceeded in one of the two following calendar years, the increased investment allowance is not eligible; this also applies to companies that are newly opened or restructured"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "207 (2) Other services to a client outside of Berlin (West) are not already available if the client is domiciled or domiciled outside of Berlin (West)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Rather, what is required is that the other service is oriented towards distance selling; this is the case if the result of the other service has an economic effect outside of Berlin"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "2 Those on 30 or 40 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "increased investment allowance 208 (1) Because of the terms research and development, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "118 pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "For the granting of the increased investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 1 Letter b BerlinFG, it is sufficient if the relevant asset is indirectly used for research or development; Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "119 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "209 (2) The investment allowance is 40 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the acquisition or production costs of the movable assets acquired or manufactured in the financial year, insofar as the acquisition or production costs do not exceed the amount of 500,000 DM, and 30 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the acquisition or production costs exceeding this amount (Section 19 (1) sentence 4 no.1 letter b BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "To take into account the limit of DM 500,000 per calendar year when calculating the 40 or 30 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "increased investment allowance applies to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "132 analogously"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "210 (3) For the acquisition of new intangible assets, an investment allowance according to \u00a7 19 BerlinFG is not granted even if these assets are used exclusively for research or development"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, for such intangible assets - even if they serve the beneficiary purposes in a permanent establishment in Berlin (West) - an investment allowance according to \u00a7 4 InvZulG (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "122 to 132) come into consideration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3 Prerequisites for Remaining and Use 211 (1) The prerequisite for the granting of the increased investment allowance is that the beneficial asset also meets the additional requirements for the increased investment allowance at least three years after its acquisition or manufacture"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If an asset partially fulfills the additional requirements of Section 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 1 Letter a and partially those of Section 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 No. 1 Letter b BerlinFG within the three-year period, an investment allowance of 25% is required for the asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "(BFH judgment of 17 December 1976 - BStBl II 1977 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "234)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "If an asset partly fulfills the additional requirements for an increased investment allowance and partly only the conditions for an investment allowance of 10% within the three-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": ", only the investment allowance of 10 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "to grant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "212 (2) An increased investment allowance can also be considered for a beneficiary movable asset if, within three years of its acquisition or manufacture, it is sold to the fixed assets of another permanent establishment located in Berlin (West) or in one of Berlin (West) occupied business premises of another is used (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "171)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for this is that, by the end of the three-year period, a sold asset continues to be in the purchaser's business premises and a rented or leased business good in the business premises of the tenant or lessee fulfills the usage requirements necessary for the increased investment allowance (BFH judgment of 6 5 1977 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "592)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "213 (3) If the actual use of an asset in the relevant three-year period does not correspond to the use assumed in the decision on the application for an investment allowance and an investment allowance that is too high has therefore been granted (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the asset should be used in the area of \u200b\u200bresearch or development, but in fact it has partly also been used in the production area), the investment allowance is to be reclaimed insofar as only a lower investment allowance can be considered due to the lack of the conditions for use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "190 Example 2 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "IV Special requirements for the 25 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "increased investment allowance for immovable assets 214 (1) The 25 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "increased investment allowance for preferential immovable assets can only be claimed if the immovable assets or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the removed or newly manufactured parts or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "in the case of subsequent production work, the immovable assets on which the subsequent production work has been carried out in the beneficiary's own commercial operation at least three years after their production or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "after completion of the subsequent production work to more than 80%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "serve directly for research or development within the meaning of Section 51 Paragraph 1 No. 2 Letter u Sentence 4 EStG (Section 14 Paragraph 2 Sentence 1 No. 2 Letter a double letter dd BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Because of the terms research and development, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "118 pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "215 (2) If the immovable assets or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the removed or newly manufactured parts do not consistently exceed 80% within the three-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "research or development, but more than 80 v. Chr"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "in total, the requirements of \u00a7 14 Paragraph 2 Clause 1 No. 2 Letter a Double Letter aa to ee BerlinFG, then for immovable assets or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the extensions or extensions an investment allowance of 20 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "to grant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The same applies mutatis mutandis to other subsequent production work on immovable assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Example: From the time of completion, during the three-year period of use, a building is used to the full for internal purposes, for research and development purposes 600 sqm, for production purposes 250 sqm, for sales purposes 150 sqm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "The building is no longer used for more than 80 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Research or development purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "An investment allowance of 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "is out of the question"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "However, the building serves a total of more than 80 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "beneficiary purposes (research or development and manufacturing); an investment allowance of 20 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the production costs are granted (Section 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 3 No. 2 BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "216 (3) If, during the relevant three-year period, the proportion of the use of the immovable property required for the granting of the increased investment allowance is reduced, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "190 accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "217 (4) For preferential immovable assets as well as for extensions and extensions and other subsequent production work, for which the application for building permit was made before 14 1985, the investment allowance is 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "the manufacturing costs; If an application for a building permit is not required under building law, the construction work begins in its place (see Section 31, Paragraph 19 BerlinFG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "Final provision As far as in the BMF letter of 5 5 1977 (BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "246), 20 5 1977 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "281), 10 8 1977 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "428), 18 10 1977 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "488), 4 11 1977 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "550), 25 9 1978 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "383, 28 12 1979 (BStBl 1980 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "3), 20 12 1979 (BStBl 1980 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "11), 14 5 1980 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "231), 29 3 1985 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "113), 3 5 1985 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "188) and from 26 11 1985 (BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "683) on the application of \u00a7\u00a7 1 4 4a and 5 InvZulG as well as \u00a7 19 BerlinFG, this letter takes its place"}, {"meta": {"name": "0077319.xml"}, "text": "--- Tax promotion lawsBremenRhineland-Palatinate North Rhine-Westphalia SaarlandLower SaxonyBaden-W\u00fcrttembergHamburgHesseSchleswig-HolsteinBerlin Federal Republic"}]